column6: Kleancolor Nail Polish NEON Colors Lot of 6! Lacquer Neon Collection + Free Earring Gift
column13: I fell in love with the colors (and the price) online
column14:
I fell in love with the colors (and the price) online. However, the colors and the quality of the polish do not perform well.

A few things about my relationship with Nail Polish:

- I have 30-50 colors at any given time.
- If a color doesn't look good with my skin color, if I get bored of it, or I notice it doesn't get much play in the rotation, I give it to my nieces.
- I LOVE bright colors. I also love Blues.
- I love opaque polishes.
- I always use base coat and top coat, and usually use 2 coats of color.

So this purchase:

- The Green paints on very, very thin, almost sheer. The first coat makes my nails look diseased. Additional coats didn't do much for color saturation. It was very ugly.

- The Yellow was sheer as well, and despite rolling the bottle before application, the color seemed to pool in the corners. I had to use 3 coats and it just looked too iridescent. I was hoping for a bright Daisy yellow - not a dull Banana or Pale Lemon and this was a mix of both.

- Red, Purple, Blue, Pink - were opaque (as seen in the photo), but the polish is very goopy and takes forever to dry. I make sure that the brush isn't dripping and do 3 simple strokes - side/side/center.

- The Red looks "cherry red" online but the actual color was a pinkish orange. I'd rather it have been a bright NEON orange as the photo suggested.

- The Pink is very pretty.

- The Blue is very summery.

- All colors chip very easily - after only a few hours, and I avoid using my nails as tools, wear non-latex gloves for cleaning, and "baby" my nails for the first 24 hours. I also tried several base and top coats to help prevent the chipping, but found no solution.

I am overall VERY disappointed. If you're looking for something to last a few hours, it might work, but for what I wanted - bright NEON colors that lasted a few days - it was not a good purchase.

column13: Smells a bit iffy, but results are wonderful.
column14:
I use this oil at the end of my morning and night routines by mixing it into my moisturizer. I have very dry and sensitive skin. And when it comes down to it, I need a very heavy moisturizer to get me through my day with showing skin flaking. Unfortunately, when I use very heavy moisturizers, they are greasy and never seem to sink in. A couple drops of oil in a medium moisturizer though, is perfection for me. I have tried several different ones including, jojoba, argan, apricot and now rosehip.

First of all, this does't smell like roses and most people might say it smells straight up bad. Like some sort of fruit gone bad. I've grown used to it though and it doesn't bother me. It's a dark orange color, and slightly thicker than some other oils. The bottle itself is pretty standard glass with a dropper.

Where this oil shines though, is how it makes the skin look so plump and moisturized and healthy. I add 3 drops to my morning moisturizer and 10 to my nightly one. I have had no breakouts whatsoever, it even helps old acne marks heal faster. And my skin looks so nourished.

If you can get over the smell, this is a great oil to use.

column6: Silk'n Flash & Go Permanent Hair Removal System
column14:
I am so pleasantly surprised! I was expecting maybe a reduction in the thickness of my body hair but it's even better than that! I have very white skin and black hair. I started using the device the day I got it and saw results on my armpits right away. I haven't needed to shave my underarms in a month and a half. My bikini line has much deeper roots but that too has stopped regrowing hair. I little exfoliating removed the left over stubble (because you need to shave before you use it the dead root of the hair is left in the skin). I can wear my bathing suit without being embarrassed by stubble or my bikini lines five o'clock shadow. I feel more feminine at the beach. It rarely stings me at all, only when I accidentally zap a dark freckle. I do close my eyes or look away when I pull the trigger because the flash is very bright. I am normally skeptical of beauty tech but it's been a dream of mine to take a shower and enjoy it instead of feeling like it was a chore because of shaving, that's why I'm so happy with it, because it really has worked for me. Also no more ingrown hairs. I am starting my legs now. I'll post more results and maybe some photos once I see how well it works there.

UPDATE : it's been about a year and a half (1-26-17) and I haven't shaved my armpits in a year. They are baby smooth! I did my arms and bikini line, a little work on my face, even my toes and hands, my upper legs and have finally started my lower legs. It's slow going. I really do wish the area the device covered during a pulse were bigger but I don't even mind. It's been working so well all this time I can't complain. I saved my legs for last because I knew it was going to take the longest but even now, I already don't have to shave my legs but once every two weeks and I've only been doing a portion of each leg every 6 days or so (whenever I find a moment) . I used up the bulb that came with it a long time ago and bought the longer lasting one which is still going strong.

I love it. No ingrown hairs, no balancing in the shower to shave, no razor burn. We have a pool and its great to be able to throw on a bikini if friends show up and not worry bikini line stubble. And I actually enjoy my baths and showers now because I can relax and enjoy the bubbles instead of shaving.

Anyway, I totally approve.e it. No ingrown hairs, no balancing in the shower to shave, no razor burn. We have a pool and its great to be able to throw on a bikini if friends show up and not worry bikini line stubble. And I actually enjoy my baths and showers now because I can relax and enjoy the bubbles instead of shaving. Anyway, I totally approve.

column14:

Not like this though, it was so bad my face actually hurt to move.

My whole forehead was covered in tiny pimples, my problem areas (jaw and cheeks) were so bad that even my makeup couldn't cover the mess. I had 2 actual cystic acne pimples which still aren't fully healed. I don't know what's in this soap that cloggs pores so badly but it should be avoided at all costs. I have 2 scars forming where the cysts were.

column6: Remington PF7400 F4 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Black
column14: I have a love/hate relationship with electric shavers.  I started out years ago with Remington shavers back when they were made like a tank.  I would've hoped the technology improved a bit while maintaining quality.  I can't say that is true for this shaver.  It is the same tech from years ago, built into a slimmer but less durable package.  The charging cable is like it never occurred to them to have an elegant dock like they used to have.  Instead you put a plug in the bottom and they give you a cheap piece of plastic to stand the razor in upside down.  It is very unstable.  So much so, my new razor toppled off the shelf onto the floor and went into pieces.  I don't think anything is broken, but the foils and everything all came off and I still haven't found all the pieces which is also ridiculous there are so many.  I wanted to like this Remington, but compared to the Norelco I have sitting happily on the counter in a beautiful dock, I can't say I do.

column13: Beautyinside Foundation Sponge Helps Get To Hard To Reach Areas And Applies Makeup Very Well!
column14:
This Beautyinside Foundation Sponge is so much easier to use then regular makeup sponges. Most sponges don't have handles which makes applying makeup extremely messy and rather annoying and since this sponge comes with a handle it makes this sponge stand out from it's competitors. You only get 1 sponge and the color you get is random which for me personally wasn't that big of a deal plus the color I got is really pretty. This sponge has a point on one side which helps reach the hard to reach areas and it's also easy to apply all over coverage. The sponge also applies makeup really good without making my skin look like it's caked with makeup! This sponge isn't harsh on my sensitive skin either which is a great thing. The sponge is also very easy to clean which I use baby shampoo to clean all my brushes/sponges. I would definitely recommend this Beautyinside Foundation Sponge!

column13: Unimpressed by customer service and questionable quality control but it does do the job of straightening hair
column14: Good points - It heats up well (in the US - not yet tested in Europe but this is why I purchased this model). The lighted display is easy to read and it is light weight. I appreciate that it comes with all the adapter plugs for Europe/Asia as these can cost $20 each. Bad points and the reason for only giving it 3 stars: the instructions booklet that comes with this product is replete with very poor english - spelling mistakes and wrong grammar. While this is not important for understanding how to use the product as it is so self explanatory, this smacks to me of a company that is overseas and not making any effort to produce a quality product. If they couldn't take the time and resources to properly edit the instruction booklet, have they an equally "caveat emptor" attitude to the quality of straightener? Secondly, I see that Amazon lists this as dual voltage  however in the instruction booklet it clearly states that this product is intended for use in households with 110 volts (US). I wrote to the company using the email address they give for customers and asked them to confirm that it is indeed dual voltage. No reply. Sent a second email a week later - no reply. So basically I would say no customer service  -- good luck if you ever needed to contact them for a failed product...

column14: I love this stuff, I suffer from hormonal cystic acne, and am trying to cope with breakouts now that I've decided to stop taking my antibiotic. When I have clusters of breakouts, I put this on a cotton ball and apply to affected areas. If there are just a few, I apply to a q-tip and dab on. The smell isn't great, but I'm familiar with the smell of some of the ingredients (such as tea tree oil) that may be off putting at first. Also, the bottle is consistent with that of essential oils, so I'm also used to the way you have to carefully drop out the treatment. This spot treatment stops the growth and inflammation of my breakouts dead in its tracks, it really works for me. I put it on morning and night right before my moisturizer, and have seen drastic improvements in my skin!

column14: If your color just needs a boost or you want to even it out, this is the perfect product. Some online directions say to mix it with water, but that is incorrect - apply it to towel dried hair and after about 30 minutes carefully and completely rinse it out.  The color will last about 3 or 4 shampoos, especially if you use a co-wash or cleansing conditioner.  You can also use your normal conditioner as a shampoo, just don't expect it to get sudsy.  The Clairol Beautiful color will gradually fade.

column6: Odaban Antiperspirant Spray 30 Ml
column13: I felt like I was constantly trying to mask my under arm ...
column14: I have always been a really sweaty person. I would sweat for no apparent reason, especially under my arms. I would have to change my shirt or undershirt at least once every day to feel dry and clean. I had tried the prescription strength of all of the major brands of antiperspirant deodorants and none of them worked. I felt like I was constantly trying to mask my under arm sweat and smell. I went on the hunt for something other than an antiperspirant deodorant. That's when I came upon Odaban. After reading the reviews of other people on the product I decided it was worth a try. I have never been more happy with a product. It has literally changed my life. The first few weeks of using it, my under arms would feel irritated and itchy because I was using it every day, but they weren't sweating! I've now been using it for over a year and only spray it on about once a week and my underarms are ALWAYS dry. It's amazing. Just remember that if your underarms are itching out of control or they start peeling, you're using it too often. I do use a natural (Toms) non antiperspirant deodorant in the morning, just to stay fresh smelling throughout the day. If you are constantly dealing with underarm sweat and want to stop it, definitely try this product!

column6: Thinksport Sunscreen SPF 50+
column14: This is one of the first sun blocks of any kind I have used.  We have always seemed to do just fine using protective clothing and avoiding the sun from 10 to 2 and so on, but my new baby/toddler is very fair and I worried that would not be enough to keep him sun safe. I did a lot of online research and this product was at the top of most lists, and the price was decent here on Amazon, so we tried it. Well, this product just did not work out for us at all. It was thick and pasty and just never rubbed in well. I understand the way a physical sunblock is supposed to work but  this sat on top of our skin and appeared ashy on even the fairest of my family. None of us particularly liked the smell, which reminded me of orange creamsicles. It wasn't awful but it just kind of smelled odd for a sunblock.  But the biggest issue was either the actual sunblock protection seemed to be nil and/or there is something in the ingredient list that causes skin reactions, because we all got a terrible rash/sunburn that took weeks to heal.  I am almost 40 and neither I nor my 10 and 7 year olds have ever had a sunburn not using sunblock, and we all got one the first time we used this!  It is certainly possible we are particularly sensitive to some ingredient since other people seem to like this a lot, but based on our experience I could not recommend this product.

column13: TERRIBLE Product - save your money or use another dye.
column14: I bought two boxes of dye, since I have long hair - which is usually enough (and some left over) with other dyes. I thought that, because it was a creme, it would saturate my hair without much problem - WRONG. I could have used four boxes, maybe, but because the dye doesn't naturally saturate, and you have to work the dye in to get it to moved from the ONE SPOT is stays in, you end up missing spots, is bad for you, because this stuff is NOT supposed to be massaged into your scalp AND it gets everywhere as you're pulling at your hair to work the dye into spots that it didn't cover - not to mention, it just didn't "take" to part of my hair. My hair is now two different colors, and I have to wait to dye it again. Thank god my hair is curly and it can pass as highlights for now. I've been dying my hair since I was 16 (I'm 33) and I know a few things about hair dye. This stuff is horrible. After going red for a while, I wanted to get close to my natural color, which matches up to the color on the box... except, this color is BLACK on my hair, not brown. Never again.

column6: Nair Ultimate Moroccan Argan Oil with Orange Blossom Rinseable Wax Kit
column13: Why did you ruin a good thing Nair??
column14: I was a big fan of the old Nair wax that had the peach and melon extract.  The excess wax easily washed off with water.  I felt like I was becoming a real pro!  After running out, I went to every store I could think of, but could not find a new jar.  It seemed like this Moroccan Argan Oil had replaced them all.  So I figured I'd give it a whirl.  The roll on wax feature IS SILLY.  Why?  Because this wax that "washes off easily with soap and  water does anything but!  The wax itself is effective. (hence the 3 stars) But every time I'm showering after I wax I find myself saying, "I curse you Nair!"  The excess will not wash off!  That's pretty much what happens with the roll on piece also.  I could not remove 100% of the excess so I gave up.  Reusable cloth strips?  Yeah Nair, that's exactly what I want to do.  Soak the hair I just pulled off my body in a cup or sink, and then take a 25 minute shower angrily scrubbing off wax.  And THEN get out of the shower and scrub the excess hair that has not separated from the strip.  This is not a short process.  What I'm doing now (until the bottle is gone) is heat up the wax and put it into the old wax jar, and use one of those wooden (popsicle stick) applicators.  You have to consider the consumer Nair.  Most of us aren't pros.  The old wax that rinsed away EASILY with water was terrific!

column14: I'm going to say for how cheap One Man Show is as a cologne...it's got a lot of scent character.It's strong and lasts as a very gentlemanly cologne.I don't consider it unique or original as it reminds me of Krizia Uomo and the Van Cleef & Arpel's Pour Homme mixed together.It comes off as soapy and green from pine with a note of myrrh incense and rose.The myrrh starts to get too strong along with the rose as it loses it's soapy and green character.Then it develops some nice mildly sweet and spicy notes to it.I never got to try this cologne when I was younger as part of my generation.Basically though it's very reminiscent to Krizia Uomo except it's out of control in being cloying and just off it's leash.The association I get from VC&A Pour Homme is the hefty rose and soapy vibe...no leather though.Oh One Man Show is what I like of the late 70's/early 80's gentleman scents but I think I'm still sticking with Krizia Uomo which is still inexpensive.

column13: Well Made Foot File - A Bit On The Small Side
column14:
This is a very nice foot file. The solid build is great and the two sanding surfaces are sturdy. The metal one reminds me of a microplane or a miniature cheese grater. I thought it would hurt using it on my heel, but it turned out to be fine. The second surface was sand-paper like for fine sanding? I liked every color the product came in except the bronze. Guess which one I got? Yup. Bronze. The company could offer a color choice. A lot of people like bronze. I'm just not one of them.

Unfortunately I found a few things wrong with it that I think the company could improve upon. This is why I marked it down to four stars instead of five. The first is the color choice thing as I explained above. I'd rather have a choice. Secondly, its size is fairly small. If you have tiny feet, its perfect for you. If you have larger ones though, this small file is a lot of work to hold onto, sand with, and smooth out your feet. I would only recommend it for a small woman, not for a male or a larger female with bigger feet.

column6: Veet VTSH8705 Touchably Smooth Mains Epilator
column14:
[[VIDEOID:d4d5a6bf0f48e65316abdd2933dbef99]]This Veet Touchably Smooth Epilator is different but not in a bad way. I really didn't know what to expect when I tried it for the first time because I had never used an epilator before. I was pretty nervous, maybe even a little scared but I gave it a shot and I am glad that I did.

This epilator is easy to start using. It comes with a USB charging cord that plugs into my electrical outlet. I charged mine fore a few hours before the first use. Prior to using the epilator I sprayed the pre-epilation spray all over the area I was going to use it on. This spray smelled like Vicks Vapor Rub and had a cooling effect to my legs before and after using the epilator. This epilator comes with 2 zone heads; one for larger areas and one for smaller areas.

The epilator can be used on a high or low setting. I recommend starting with the low setting if you have never used an epilator before. About 5 minutes after spraying my legs with the pre-epilation spray I decided to give this product a try. It wasn't extremely painful, just a little uncomfortable feeling. From reading, that is common with all epilators. After a few minutes the sensation did not seem to bother me anymore. You definitely get used to it after a while. This epilator basically rips the hair out like waxing would but is supposed to not disturb the cells of the epidermis.

After using the epilator I used the little cleaning brush that was included in the box to brush the loose hairs out and into the trash. I then rinse the head of the epilator under running water. Start to finish the process was simple and easy. Don't give up after your first try using the epilator. With continued use, you will get more and more used to the sensation you feel while using it. I have used mine several times so far because I am doing small to medium sections at a time. I have noticed that with each use the feel of it is bothering me less and less.

I received this product at a discounted price in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.unted price in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.

column13: Soaks In Quickly, With No \STICKY\" Feel"
column14:
Both myself and my husband were very pleased with our first time using your product. It was one of those days that was semi-cloudy, and not particularly humid - so he didn't feel that he had been sweating profusely and needed to re-apply. My husband is rather fair skinned and normally burns quite easily. He did not get burned at all. When I use a sunscreen product, I expect it to protect me from the sun, but what I particularly noticed & liked about the Sport Sunscreen is that it didn't feel very "heavy" when I applied it. Normally, I really hate the feel of sunscreens, but this one quickly soaked into my skin and I had no heavy, gooey coating on my skin. column13: NICE amounts of steam, easy to use, great unit!
column14:
[[VIDEOID:7202f2f9c1367976e19d5fc201b8d216]]This review is for the MIRA Nano Ionic Facial Steamer.

This is a GREAT facial steamer. I never really knew I needed a facial steamer till I owned one. Now I can't live without this!

This steamer is high quality and made well. The base is strong and solid. You can feel the quality of the materials and also the fact that the unit has a nice weight won't let it tip over while you are getting your face steamed. It's a great design.

The back compartment slips out easily and fills with distilled or purified water very simply. Just unscrew the lid and fill, pop the cartridge back into the compartment. The steamer is now ready to go if you have it plugged into a wall outlet.

Flip the ON switch and wait approx 40 seconds. It takes a bit to get the steam thick and heavy. Once it is ready, place your face 8 inches away from the outlet. You can feel the warm steam like a soft cloud across your face. Immediately you can tell it's starting to work.

I LOVE this steamer if I have had sinus issues the prior day or have a cold or puffy eyes. Literally the steam within 5 minutes takes away any problems I have had brewing up in my head. It's not just for pore extraction but also for wellness too!

When I want to do a facial, I take a steamy shower, come out, steam my face a little longer, then use my pore extraction tools and face mask. I feel like a new person, and my skin looks SO SOFT and full of hydration!

This steamer is a MUST HAVE! 5/5 stars for design, functionality and QUALITY! This would make a GREAT gift for someone also!

column13: Excellent.  Highly Recommended.  Careful When Cleaning (See Review)
column14:
The instructions on this could have been a little more clearly written, and bullet pointed so you could follow along step by step as you go, but other than that there's no complaint at all.

The results were stellar (great fit), and I woke up without blood in my mouth from damage to gums due to teeth grinding (no tension headache, either).

I'd make sure to read through the instructions a few times to visualize the steps, and to mark a 1, 2, 3, etc. for each step on the instructions, but other than that I was impressed.

I expected this to take some getting used to, but it was easy.

They also state right in the literature that comes with it that they want it work out for you and will replace or return if needed (if you mess it up on re-sizing, for instance). I didn't have to resize at all so that was a non-issue.

Very pleased with the result and the fact that there are two more to mold in the future when needed.

ONE WARNING:

I left this to clean in a tray of water just hot from the tap and at the end of the day it had shrunk to the point my back teeth at either end and up and down weren't covered. The takeaway here is to use cold water when cleaning, not hot. Hot should only be for molding.

column14: I wrote a review some time ago. I have to write again. This stuff is amazing and I'm disappointed to see others giving it bad reviews. I also love the fact that it is cruelty free as I am an animal advocate.

column6: Amara Organics Facial Cleanser with 15% Vitamin C, 6 fl. oz.
column14:
I have been using Armana Organics products for a few months now, and so far I really like this skin care line. I consider my skin to be normal to sometimes oily, a little sensitive, and to have some scarring and discoloration.
These Vitamin C products have really made a difference in my skin tone and kept my skins hydration regulated. I really am addicted to vitamin c serums and toners!! Now I have finally found a great vitamin C cleanser..
This serum also includes... aloe, rosehip oil and tea tree oil... Some of my favorite ingredients! Tea tree oil works wonders for redness. When you first pump out the product, it is a little thick. Do not use too much, I found that 2 small pumps gives you plenty of cleanser to work with. It does not get too sudsy, which I like. I cant stand a facial cleanser that wont rinse away, and leaves your skin full of residue.
I massage the product around my face with my fingertips, in a circular motion. I found that this cleanser is an awesome make up remover!!!
It feels like there are micro sized scrubbers, washing your face for you....It left my skin feeling very refreshed and resilient.
My skin did feel very tight and toned after cleansing with this product... I followed with a vitamin C toner and then a vitamin C serum...
I liked all aspects of Amara Organics Vitamin C Cleanser....I received tis item free, for my unbiased and honest opinions!

column6: SOCAL SO CHILL by HOLLISTER 1.7 oz (50ml) EAU DE COLOGNE SPRAY for Men NEW IN BOX
column14:
Let's start off with the order. I ordered this hoping that it'd smell something like the regular brown SoCal. When I went into my local Hollister store, the manager described this cologne as a lighter version of the original SoCal but that unfortunately, it was all sold out. Originally, I had wanted the original SoCal but I came to the realization that it might be a bit too strong; depending on how much I spray of course. Don't get me wrong I still love the way the brown SoCal smells. But I changed my mind and decided to get this. The price is a few bucks cheaper than it would be in the store so that's a thumbs up lol. I looked to buy it off of Amazon and here it was. They didn't have many reviews or complete ones for that matter, so I was taking a large risk buying something that I wasn't even sure I'd like. Also, I've decided to write my 100% review of this order, in detail so future buyers will know exactly what they're getting into and buying. I should probably be typing this review after a whole day or week after owning the product but I'm just so eager and impatient to do this lol

My order was shipped less than a day later after I placed it which is great in my opinion. I was very anxious to smell what this cologne would smell like, they didn't have it in stores, mind you, so I couldn't test it out there. Unfortunately, my package was delayed a day or two. I'm not sure if that's because of the seller or USPS lol but it's no biggie. I got my package this afternoon and I rushed to open it. It was very, very secure as it was wrapped in several layers of Styrofoam and bubble wrap; not to mention the durable cardboard box the cologne itself comes in. The box is a little difficult to open so you might just have to use a knife to open it.

I sprayed just a little bit on my wrist. It doesn't smell much too like the brown SoCal. Is it called SoCal Jake? I'm not sure lol but it doesn't really smell like it. It smells very good at first, even with just a little bit applied. It has it's own distinct smell from the other SoCal/ Hollister colognes and I find that great. Although it does smell good, I don't recommend spraying too much because then it'll probably turn people away from the strength, rather than attracting them. Two hours later, and I can still smell it. I hope it lasts long. It doesn't really project but that's fine, someone would have to get close in order to really smell it. The bottle isn't small either and should be lasting me a long while. It's a few inches taller than the length of the average palm. Maybe about 5 inches? Yeah that's about it, I don't have a ruler on me at the moment lol.

I'm giving the seller a 9/10 and the cologne a 4/5. I really like it and I can't wait to go out and see what others have to say about it's distinct yet chill and light smell. If you're looking for a nice smelling cologne that's not too strong and not too light then this is the one for you! Great job Amazing Beauty!

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column14: I received a sample of this product free for review thanks to Secret.  I'm already a Secret fan.  I enjoy the fragrances from the Destinations collection quite a bit.  It's never really bothered me in the past that solids will sometimes dry out and leave little deodorant crumbs behind, because I almost never show my armpits.  I may switch to a clear gel after all.  I like the way this covers and dries without a trace.  The scent is very light.  A little like cucumber-melon.  Either way, they offer the Destinations collection in clear gel form too, so I can have my pick.  I've enjoyed my tiny sample.  If I hadn't told my boyfriend that I'm not allowed to buy any new deodorant until I finish what I have, I'd go out and get another of these.  Also, if you're a girl going natural, it's nice to have something that won't cake in your hair.  Look, I'm a hippie too, but just because I look like one doesn't mean I smell like one.  You don't have to rub crystals in your pits to avoid deodorant residue.  Secret's got you covered.

column6: Redken Shades EQ 9NB Irish Creme 2oz
column14: This is a good shade to mix with 9V to tone overly gold blond hair.  I didn't want to eliminate all the warmth from my hair, just tone it to a warm neutral hue, hence I added 9NB to 9V (violet base, which neutralizes gold) in equal parts.  I left it on for 10 minutes and it came out perfect, exactly how I'd hoped.  This is my first time using Shades EQ and I have to say that it left my hair really shiny and soft and not overly ashy at all.  I have no idea how 9NB would work on its own but I do know it has a neutral warm base (usually brown).  My blond hair always becomes way too gold a few weeks after my hair color appointment and it's nice to be able to tone it myself.  I prefer a toner rather than the temporary effects of purple shampoo, which can leave my hair way too ashy if left on too long.  Toners usually last for several weeks and I hope Shades EQ is no exception.  This brand has been recommended many times on makeupalley.com so I decided to give it a try.  I now have a huge bottle of the processing solution, which was really economical.  Doing it myself is much cheaper and I like the results a lot better.  I highly recommend Shades EQ.

column6: Gillette Clinical Anti-Perspirant Deodorant, Ultimate Fresh Advanced Solid 1.70 oz
column13: Once the best AND and now possibly the worst!
column14:
This is the only deodorant I've been using for years. It is hands down the absolute best deodorant, period. The scent is fantastic and it really lasts super long.

Here's the problem. It's changed. It used to come in a darker navy blue box, and now it comes in a lighter silver box. If your store has both, pick the older darker navy box. Whatever Gillette has done, they've royally screwed up something that was fantastic. I've scrolled through other reviews just to make sure it wasn't a regional issue and it doesn't seem like it is. This deodorant now heavily crusts/clumps/flakes on the actual bottle and when applying. I look down at my expensive dress shoes and belt every morning and see flakes from my deodorant all over. The worst part is that I actually dread putting it on, because the clumps/crusts/flakes on the bottle/applicator hurt your armpits when rubbing. You have to wait a couple of minutes and kind of flick your armpit hairs to shake off any flakes.

This went from being a Godsend of a product to one of the most aggravating and frustrating daily products I have. I called the support line and they told me this tends to happen with extreme temperature exposures and try to get it from a different store. I did. I have 4 bottles of this stuff laying around 90% full because I'm hoping the next one will be better. It's not. It's not a location/regional/store issue. The product has been changed for the worse.

If I sound dramatic, it's somewhat intentional. I'm just thoroughly disappointed and feel let down by what used to be one of my favorite products. I got my brother to use it, my dad, my uncle. I'll give it one or two more purchases, then I think I might throw in the towel. I'm tired of wasting my money.

column6: Conair Infiniti Professional Tourmaline Ceramic Curling Iron
column13: Great as Long as Your Hair is Dry
column14:
The barrel size of this curling iron is perfect for huge loose curls. Because of the size, however, it is a little difficult to use on short hair. I'm in the process of growing my hair out, so it's longer now than it was when I first starting using the curling iron and it's much easier to handle. The iron heats up very quickly, I have yet to use it on any other setting other than the hottest. I have found that even if my hair is just a little damp, the curling iron doesn't successfully curl, like it claims to do. So I would not call it a wet/dry curling iron.

The cord is plenty long for me to plug it in behind my vanity and snake up over the backside of the table. I don't find that I hit the buttons to turn it off while curling, like some other reviewers have mentioned. Overall, I really like this curling iron. Just doesn't perform as it says it does when it comes to curling damp hair.

I now mix oil in an oatmeal conditioner, I use tea tree, almond, grapeseed, jojoba or coconut usually and add 2 teaspoons to a couple ounces of conditioner add a little water and use it as a rinse and she doesn't itch to bad for a couple days.

column13: Also for some reason the pack I received stinks of plastic solvent - like the kind of smell you think you might get ...
column14:
Patterns are cute and you get a lot of them, but the stickers are somewhat flimsy and hard to remove without tearing them, and the coloured ones all seem to have their dyes a bit displaced so it just kind of ends up looking a mess. Also for some reason the pack I received stinks of plastic solvent - like the kind of smell you think you might get cancer if you breathe it in too long, you know? It's really off-putting and makes me wary to use/handle these too often lest I come down with some sort of chemical poisoning.

For the price, though, you do get a lot of cute patterns. Especially in the black and white stickers; I like the roses and butterflies the best. Durability once they're on your nails is about the same as any other decal, just use a good top coat. If you're good with a pair of tweezers to get the stickers off without ripping, and you don't mind the room reeking of chemical death when you use these (and I mean seriously, it's powerful - I've worked in industrial mining laboratories that didn't smell half this strong and we were using pure ammonium hydroxide!), then these are worth the couple bucks. Just be sure to follow good ventilation practices and ALWAYS use a quality base and topcoat.

column6: Emjoi Micro-Pedi Nano Callus Remover
column14:
I’ve told y’all before I’m a pedicure junkie. When I finally get all the correct lottery numbers on just one ticket; this girl will be getting a pedicure every single week!! Getting a pedicure is one of those wonderful relaxing indulgences that I simply adore! Since The Husband and I are retired I can only indulge in a professional pedicure every other month. However, since I spend about 99.999% of the time barefoot I don’t dare let my feet go for 2 months! I can’t even imagine how bad my feet would look if I didn’t use this. Yikes; that just gives me goosebumps just thinking about it!!
I am thrilled to share my review with you of the Emjoi; a Micro-Pedi Battery Operated Callus Remover. The Emjoi is super easy to use. If you apply too much pressure the Emjoi stops on its own. HOWEVER! You don’t need to apply pressure for this wonderful device to get rid of your dead skin. Seriously this device will have dead skin flying like crazy!
The Emjoi does such an awesome job! So much so, that the last professional pedicure I had, the technician didn’t even ask if I wanted the “extra callus remover treatment” You know these are soft feet if that’s the case!
The Emjoi Micro-Pedi not only gave me instant results but the more I use it the smoother and softer my heels feel.
The Emjoi Micro-Pedi Nano Callus Remover takes two double A batteries. Insert the batteries by simply twisting off the end. Super easy. Also changing out the roller is very simple as well; just the push of a button on the side.
Holding the Emjoi is easy because of its ergonomic design and easy grip sides.
The Emjoi works wonders! While it really buffs away dead, dry and calloused skin it does it without pain. You can’t go wrong with this one!
Disclosure: I have received a free or greatly discounted product for the purpose of this review. The opinions are 100% mine.

column14:
Great value, comes in a generous 8 ounce tub. Has a gel like whipped texture, is very thick, white and only a very faint clean smell. The smell doesn't linger long either. This has some wonderful ingredients in it. I tried to get a pic of the list I will attach to review. I really like the cream, it is awesome right now for feet and body, but not my face yet till cold weather. If you have dry skin this might be made just for you.

column14:
I've bought two of these now (from Walmart, not Amazon). They did everything I wanted them to do and more. The only problem is that the shaving heads don't stay on. The first head I used worked great for a few months, but then after time if I picked up the trimmer and held it upside down the shaving head would just fall right off. I'd put it back on but there was not "snap" or "click" affirming that it would stay in place. It would just slide on and then fall right back off.

Okay, great, the head has worn out, I'll just get a replacement head. I bought a package of replacement heads and they too would just fall right off. Okay... Maybe it's a fluke and the attachment piece that the replacement head clips onto on the trimmer itself is worn out. So I bought a second body groomer. within 2 shaves I had the exact same problem; lovely, $55.00 down the drain.

I love the product and what it's intended to do, and minus the replacement heads falling off, I would be giving this 5 stars every time without hesitation, but because of that one issue, unfortunately, I wouldn't recommend this to anyone since it can't do what it's designed to do..

column13: Looks very pretty and natural without screaming \ITS A WIG!\""
column14:
This is a really cute wig that has a nice thick bang and a soft wave to it. Right away, I was pleasantly surprised at how nice and real the hair felt when I took it out of the packaging.

The waves are very pretty, and natural looking. The best way that I can think of to describe the style of the wave is almost like when I braid my wet hair and allow it to air dry, then shake it out in the morning. The length is nice and long, and was exactly what I was looking for.

The fit of the wig is nice, and it stayed in place the whole evening that I had it on. I did add a few bobby pins just for added security, but I don't really think that was necessary for the future. It hugs my head pretty tightly on its own.

I wore this for a night out with friends, and I received a ton of compliments. Since it is the same color and length as my real hair, my friends did not even notice that I was wearing a wig. Everyone thought that I had just cut my bangs and styled my hair differently. I received one to review and I love the fact that I can toss this on when I am in a hurry and it looks like it could be my real hair.

column6: BullFrog Ultimate Sheer Body Protection, SPF 30, 5-Ounce Tube
column13: Quality CHEMICAL Sunscreen Recommended by EWG.org (NOT Particularly Water Resistant)
column14:
We were looking for a couple of CHEMICAL sunscreens that received a good review from EWG.org to supplement our PHYSICAL sunscreen we normally use (but leaves a whitish film). This Bullfrog received a 2 on their scale which is very good. It IS NOT as water-resistant as they indicate (probably closer to 30-40 minutes versus the 80 they say).

There is no whiteness left by this product; however, it does leave a sheen to your skin. This can be augmented by applying it, waiting 10 minutes or so, and then taking a paper towel or tissue and simply dabbing it once off your face (generally body shine isn't as big an issue for people). You are NOT wiping it; merely dabbing ONCE! Perhaps it would be better to say that you lay a tissue on your face, gently press, and then remove it. This was sufficient to remove 90% of the sheen.

I wore this for quite awhile and got no burn though I was wearing a baseball cap. My kids had it on and they also did not receive any burns.

column6: Derm-Essentials for Facial Seborrheic Dermatitis
column14: I'm using this product on my elbow rather than for the face.  I've had a patch on one elbow for over 20 years that has never, ever healed completely and always returns.  I like the product because it's very easy to use.  The thick consistency is a little like having a thin layer of ointment on the dry patch.  I've had no skin reactions...and I'm allergic to just about everything.  It has softened the patch up in two days time.  It's looking and feeling better so I'll continue to use it and see how much better it can get.  I also bought the companion product for some patches just above my hairline and that product is very oily & greasy requiring hair washing.  I'm going to try this product on the scalp as well because I think this will coat the area, moisturize and treat it without leaving all that greasy mess behind.  That way I can keep treating the scalp problem more often and more thoroughly without having to worry about greasy stringy hair that constantly needs washing.  Will advise how that goes and will amend my review as I see how it works.  Since nothing has worked to clear this up in 20+ years, so far this is a winner.  Just having skin that doesn't feel like razor blades with big dry clumps on it is making this product very helpful and worthwhile.

column6: Christian Dior Diorshow Maximizer Lash Plumping Serum 0.33 oz
column14: I really like this primer.  It adds volume and heft to my lashes without making them look clumpy.  I curl my lashes and apply the primer, wait for it to dry and then use a regular mascara followed by a coat of waterproof mascara to seal in the curl.  This system works really well for me.  I don't think this primer is simply a white mascara.  It seems to contain tiny fibers that adhere to lashes yet it doesn't clump when regular black mascara is applied over it.  I just make sure every lash is coated and that it's dry before applying regular black mascara.  It doesn't make regular mascara flake or rub off at all.  I also like the brush, which easily coats every lash.  All in all, I think this primer is definitely a benefit in my quest for fuller lashes.  The end result was thicker looking lashes that could have passed for falsies, lol!

column13: works, but I don't like the residue it leaves on my hands
column14:
This review is for the mango scrub.

I love body scrubs and exfoliators, but something about this one is just not doing it for me. I'm most of the way through the tub, and I can't totally put my finger on it. But here are two things I'm noticing:

(1) This is the last item I use before getting out of the shower. I rinse it off thoroughly and then towel off. And it leaves a weird feeling/residue on my hands. I really don't like the feeling, makes me not want to touch towels.

(2) It smells more like peach than mango to me.

It *is* an effective scrub. The concentration of scrubbing particles is high enough that it actually works to exfoliate. (I've been using it on my upper arms and outer thighs.) It seems to rinse off my body fairly well. It has been non-irritating to my skin and I'm able to use a moderate amount (don't have to use gobs of it or anything).

Here are the ingredients since I didn't see them on the product page:

Octyl Palmitate, Sucrose, Sodium Chloride, Sunflower Seed Oil, Silica, Mango Seed Oil, Soybean Oil, Fragrance, Benzyl Benzoate, Phenoxyethanol, Castor Seed Oil, Hexyl Cinnamal, Sweet Almond Oil, Linalool, Tocopherol, Butyl Methoxydibenzoylmethane, Amyl Cinnamal, Limonene, Capsicum Frutescens Extract, Citral, Eugenol, Amylcinnamyl Alcohol, Benzyl Alcohol, Rosemary Extract, Methyl 2-Octynoate, Propylparaben, Anisyl Alcohol, Farnesol, Geraniol, Titanium Dioxide, Yellow 5 Lake.

Ingredients you may want to watch out for: "fragrance," propylparaben, artificial dyes (i.e., yellow 5 lake).

Worth a try if you can find it on sale, but I probably won't be buying it again.

column6: 1lb Organic Shea Butter - Pure & Unrefined Grade A, Ivory African Raw Shea Butter with DIY Skin Care Recipes for Skin, Hair, Stretch Marks - Best for Making Creams, Lotions and Moisturizers - Best For Dry or Acne-Prone Skin, Eczema, Anti-Aging Agent & Nourishes Your Skin - No Additives OR Artificial Preservatives - Ethically Traded 1lbs. (16oz)
column14:
I love using raw Shea Butter as the base for home made skin cream because it's loaded with antioxidants, vitamins A, E, and other natural vitamins, and fatty acids that make it super nourishing and moisturizing while not clogging my pores. This Shea Butter is 100% pure, organic, all natural and a nice ivory color, so you can use it directly on your skin, or you can blend it with other carriers like almond, coconut, jojoba and essential oils like I do to make lotions and creams for everything from acne treatment, eczema relief, sunburn relief, to anti-aging creams. When you buy this Shea Butter the company provides a 34 page eBook filled with useful information and recipes to get you started.

Here's the basic whipped Shea Butter Cream I like to make:
4 oz. Pure Raw Unrefined Organic Shea butter
2 Tbsp Pure Fractionated Coconut Oil
15 - 20 total drops of Essential Oils - (I used 10 drops of Carrot and 5 drops of lavender and 5 drops of lemongrass.) (Experiment!!!)
Mixing Bowl & Mixer - (hand mix, food processor, or Ninja will all work)
2 clean and empty 4 oz jars with lid liners (Available in packs of 6 or more here on Amazon)

How to make it:
1. Have Raw Unrefined Shea Butter at room temperature (Do not melt or heat it!)
2. Measure 4oz and add that to your bowl and mash it with a fork like you would whipped potatoes
3. Add 2 Tbsp. Pure Fractionated Coconut Oil & mash a little more
4. Mix on high speed for about 5 minutes until mixture is creamy and well blended
5. Put whipped lotion into clean jars and close. Store in clean, dry, dark and cool place. (Room temperature is generally fine).

This Raw Shea Butter comes in a generous 1 pound size resealable bag and it's 100% pure, organic, fair trade certified, raw, unrefined, and imported from Ghana, Africa. It's a nice pure ivory color which is just perfect for skin or hair care use.

column6: Jerdon HL88NL Two-Sided Swivel LED Lighted Wall Mount Mirror with 8x Magnification, 8.5 Inch, 64.8 Ounce
column13: A nice mirror with some problems
column14:
This is a very nice makeup mirror. The quality of the mirrors are excellent, it moves and rotates smoothly. Because of the LED bulbs, the mirror is pretty thin (the units I've looked at with incandescent bulbs are much thicker), remember this is a two-sided mirror. But I have to say that the light is not particularly bright - you will need some other light source to use this mirror.
I subtracted one star for the mounting method. The back plate that mounts on the wall (sheet-rock anchors are included) is made out of pretty thin metal and it flexes. This, compounded by the fact the the mounting holes are at 3 and 9 o'clock (i.e., left and right side) not at 12 and 6 o'clock (top and bottom) where most of the stress actually occurs - makes the mount not very secure and you can actually see a gap open and close at the top where the mount housing is against the wall. Even though one of my anchors was directly into a stud - it still flexed more than I was happy with. I added a third mounting screw at 12 o'clock (top) and it made a huge difference. This is a design flaw that, while significant, can be worked around rather easily (hence I only took off 1 star).
The other flaw is the cord, or actually the plug at the end of the cord - it's a very industrial looking 3 prong plug that sticks straight out of the wall socket. This would be ok if the plug was out of sight, but by the bathroom sink the plug is almost at eye level and it doesn't look very nice. It would have been very easy for the manufacturer to use a flat 3 prong plug that would look so much better.
I had to return the first one I received because of a stain on the part of the mirror where the light shines through. Amazon sent a replacement very quickly without charging me for shipping, either way.
I probably should have taken off 2 stars but I really do like the mirror that I now have (and will like it better once I replace the cord and plug)

column6: Molor Scalp Stimulating Shampoo Brush Self-Cleaning Body and Head Massaging Scalp Brush – Soft Plastic Retractable Bristles – Ideal for Wet and Dry Hair Made In USA
column13: Great little brush with so much potential.
column14: Such a great idea and really a nice product, just poorly executed. It wouldn't take much for this to be a five star product. I ordered this because I have recently been having a lot of problems with my hair breaking, and while I work on mending my damaged hair I'm getting really tired of trying to untangle the mess of hair from my regular brush each day so it doesn't end up all over my bathroom. I've also been wanting a nice shower hairbrush to use for scalp massage and putting in special cremes and masks to help heal my hair, so that the breakage will be less of a problem. I figured this brush would kill two birds with one stone, but not quite.  Pros: -Easy clean - It's definitely infinitely easier to clean than my normal brush, I just twist the base and the bristles are tucked away leaving a flat surface to just wipe the hair away. This also makes it easy to clean the base of the brush off if you've gotten any hair product on it. -Comfortable - The bristles are harder plastic than a lot of my other brushes, which is nice for the stimulating/massage aspect, but also not unpleasant for the general brushing aspect either.  Cons: - Poor/Cheap Design - This definitely feels like a work in progress design wise, as there are many improvements that could be made which would not only make this a  five star product, but also possibly the only brush you'd ever need. However, the brush I received appeared to be cheaply manufactured, the plastic was melted and peeled a bit on one side (see photos). The bristles do not create any kind of seal with the holes they fit through, so water (and any other liquids like hair products) can easily get inside the inner portion of the brush potentially leading to issues with mold, or even just unwanted carry over of products/creams/masks/dyes if you are using it for those as I had originally planned to. Aesthetically speaking it's not pretty either, the flat side just looks like a big patent stamp, which leaves the brush looking more like some sort of industrial cleaning brush than a  personal hygene one.  All in all, I love using the brush for dry-brushing and will continue to do so, I just don't feel comfortable using it in the shower or washing it more than I have to for fear one day I'll turn the bristles up and find an unwelcome surprise.  (I received a discount on this product in exchange for my honest opinion, my reviews are 100% my own and I hope you find them helpful)

column6: Master Mosquito Repellent
column14:
The bracelets did pretty well, not sure fire but in the semi rural areas of Thailand and Laos wearing them was definitely better than not. Ended up wearing more than one (ankle + wrist) for better coverage. I bought a couple of other kinds and while these ones weren't as strong scented or effective as the ugly rubbery ones, they were a lot more discreet fashion wise. If I was feeling self conscious about looking like a nerd I would want these over the ugly rubber bands. Got them wet and the scent definitely wore off after that so would try to keep dry if possible. I can't remember how long the package said they should last for but I would guess around 5-7 days, with effectiveness tapering off the last few days of course. Definitely nice not to have to worry about constantly sweating off and reapplying mosquito repellent and I liked that they are natural and DEET free.
For the basically free package of 10 I would definitely say these were worth the price! The white and pink colours are kind of obnoxious though.

column6: effenfine Nose Hair Scissors for Trimming - Safely Trim Nose and Ears with our German Stainless Steel Scissors
column13: unsightly hairs that not only look funny, but bother both him and I
column14:
Everyone grooms themselves to a certain degree, some of us more than others. Hubby takes a mostly no-nonsense approach to grooming, with short hair on his head and no facial hair. But, his face have nooks and crannies that a razor just won't fit into, and that leaves long, unsightly hairs that not only look funny, but bother both him and I. What's a fella to do?

We thought Effenfine's facial hair would be a simple and easy solution, that didn't require cords, batteries, or a bunch of time like so many of the facial grooming products on the market. Sadly, while the Effenfine Facial Hair Scissors are a great pair of scissors, they leave much to be desired for any kind of close grooming. See, there are few things Hubby hates worse than his sharp, coarse stubble around his lips. It's annoying to him and abrasive to me with every smooch. Like 40 grit sandpaper. A razor sometimes misses at the corners of his mouth and at the peak of his top lip. So he's been using a pair of my eyebrow scissors, with fine, thin blades. We both though these Effenfine Facial Hair Scissors would be just the thing to get my other scissors back, especially with the blunted safety tip. Alas, it was not to be.

See, these Effenfine scissors are thick, heavy duty forged German stainless steel. Which means they should resist rust and corrosion for quite some time. But, it's terrible for getting up close to trim facial hair like Hubby's last pair. Which leaves the same coarse, sharp stubble as before. The lack of a pointed tip means that effectively getting into the corners of his mouth is next to impossible too. If you're just trimming the occasionally stray hair in a mustache or beard, and closeness isn't what you need, you'd be golden with these Effenfine Facial Hair Scissors. But the last nail in the coffin here for me is the price. They're significantly more expensive than I would have wanted to pay for a pair of facial hair scissors, and even moreso than a number of competitors on Amazon offering a similar product. So while they are a very capable set of scissors, and seem well made, they fail at what they're advertised for for us(facial hair). Although I was able to re-purpose them as sewing scissors, so it's not a total loss.

column13: This e-voke candle has changed my whole perception on what a candle should (and can) be!
column14:
Recently a friend gave me this e-voke candle as a gift. The gift tickled me for a couple of reasons: first, I’ve got a new obsession for candles (more about that in a minute), and second, I have raved to my friends about the company that sells them in the past so it was awesome that the gift was not only something that I love, but also from a company that I’m crazy about.
My passion for candles is relatively new. I was owned for the past 17 years by the most adorable and irritating cat on the planet: this whiskered demon would gleefully attack burning candles (I’m sure it was because he didn’t want his odd cat-smell overpowered by anything pleasant, he was a bit of a jerk at times). So for about 16 years and some odd months we were pretty much at the mercy of our feline-pyro-ninja and just sniffed longingly at friends’ beautiful candles. A month or so ago, my ear-warming nose-biting little buddy went on to Rainbow Bridge (he was a jerk and this still makes me cry, only other cat lovers would understand). Anyway, we were suddenly free to add gorgeously welcoming candles back into our home: and did we ever! We bought a lot of beautifully scented decorative candles. I was, at first, pleased with just simply being able to have them again. After a week or two a couple of things occurred to me: most candles aren’t as aromatic after the first time you burn them, and most candles don’t last very long. I assumed that those shortcomings were universal to candles but I was so wrong! My friend gave me this e-voke candle in a Minty Koala scent and I am now, officially, a candle snob: I will never settle for being disappointed with a candle again. This e-voke is just simply the best candle I have ever used. The scent is incredible: a minty-citrusy blend with warm undertones and is every bit as strong and aromatic every time I burn it! And, total bonus, the e-voke lasts (I have burned mine for hours and it’s still way over half full).
The best part, even better than how wonderful and consistent the scent is, and how long it has lasted, is that when I blow out my candle at night I can use the beautifully scented oil as a massage oil (or as a wonderful moisturizer). The oil feels luxurious and silky, the warmth makes it absorb into my skin beautifully, and the scent gets richer and deeper on my skin. This was one of the best gifts ever!n how wonderful and consistent the scent is, and how long it has lasted, is that when I blow out my candle at night I can use the beautifully scented oil as a massage oil (or as a wonderful moisturizer). The oil feels luxurious and silky, the warmth makes it absorb into my skin beautifully, and the scent gets richer and deeper on my skin. This was one of the best gifts ever!

column14: It took me a while to write this review this product, because I wanted to make sure I wasn't doing a knee-jerk reaction to the product. Now, I'm not a particularly old woman - I'm 25 - however, I've been through enough stress that my face doesn't necessarily look its age. I have dark circles and wrinkles in places that I feel should not be there at my age. I'm also unfortunate enough to have sensitive skin, so a lot of skin care products don't play nice with my face and I end up looking worse than when I started.  So I decided to take my time with this one, as it's supposed to be a long-term product being anti-aging and all. I will say that I was pleased the product didn't damage my skin in any way, and it did make it feel very soft and pleasant to the touch. It doesn't have an unpleasant odor, either.  Is it a miracle worker? Nah, I wouldn't say that. It didn't magically get rid of anything, but my face does look brighter, and my dark circles don't look as noticeable as they did after maybe two weeks' worth worth of usage. It doesn't leave a gross feeling, either, which some anti-aging serums I have used has done in the past.  I was hesitant to try this product out (discounted for unbiased review) because no anti-aging serum has been good enough for me to want to continue to use it. However, I feel that the amount of product that you get for the price, along with the refreshed feeling I get when using the serum, I feel that it is a good purchase and I plan to purchase another bottle once this one runs out.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14:
I was offered to test this shaver from promotional campaign from the brand and as soon as I received the package, I ripped the package open put the shaver to charge at the very first outlet I could find, the base and the shaver fit snugly together I didn't even have to read the manual, well shaver was FLAT no power at all so I had to patiently wait for a full charge while reading the manual. 1 hour late my shaver was blinking green and green means GO!!!!

I flew up in front of a mirror with a 4-5 day beard, ill put this puppy to a test, lets see if it can handle a MANS face, not this 3 day promise as it was saying online and on the box.

BZZZZZ BZZZZZ BZZZZZ BZZZZ 10 minutes later I was still shaving just because it was fun to play with my new toy from Braun.

I felt my skin it was smooth not razor smooth maybe I expected too much from a shaver, I had to use a razor over my Adams apple, I was kinda disappointed shouldn't this clear all this especially after shaving for 10 minutes. I put the shaver to clean, popped off the head with a click of a button and tapped it on the sink, it sure was full of stubble, I put the shaver in the base again and it recommended a 3 drop clean cycle so I kicked that off. I waited 2 days before my next shave, just wanted to see how my skin reacted, NOT A MARK or RASH which is nice I always get a little rash from a razor.

Second shave was easy and it took everything I had grown, even the Adams apple problem from before so it seems that the 3 day beard guarantee counts for me too, this shaver will leave you smooth if your beard is no older than 3 days, it will not leave you with baby smooth skin, that still takes a razor but it does the job to perfection as expected from a shaver and the big plus is the non irritated skin.

So why isn't this rated 5 stars.

doesn't leave a baby-face shave which I kinda expected from a high end shaver, BUT it does give a clean shave without foam, gel, hot water and expensive razor-blades so its really a question about preference, I CHOOSE Braun, the skin irritation vs a very small stubble i can deal with that

Thomasquestion about preference, I CHOOSE Braun, the skin irritation vs a very small stubble i can deal with that Thomas

column6: Philips Norelco Multigroom Series 5100
column13: Trims the head and neck alright, but isn't that good overall. VERY SMALL.
column14:
I purchased this model several months ago as a replacement for an old Remington trimmer. My father and I both use it often for preshaving, and I also use it for my hair.

The Multigroom 5100 turned out quite a bit smaller than I expected, along with its attachments. Never held a multipurpose trimmer so small before, and it was quite light too. Probably wouldn't survive a fall. The glossy finish on the front and neck looks good for marketing but it is not practical for grip nor age, thanks to fingerprints and small scratches. Thankfully the back has grooves and is matte, but some of the attachments face a different way, which is weird and took me a second to realize when it wouldn't go on right. The accessories also feel extremely cheap and somewhat fragile. The guide combs are flimsy and could probably break if you didn't know how to adjust them properly. The heads have perpetually wet glue on the inside, which was funny to discover. Yeah, glue. Doesn't even look like it needed it. The charging cord is probably the most pathetic, little, weightless thing I've ever held; feels quite warm after a charge and it barely stays inside the socket.

The charge time on this is very long, necessitating an overnight charge every once in a while. To me, this isn't a big deal. People who use this on the go probably will not appreciate it, and it's still something that other trimmers do a lot better. The indicator lights do their job well to warn you of low battery and a complete charge. I've had no issue with the trimmer prematurely failing on me as of yet.

The primary head provides a great, smooth trim with no pulling or irritation, even for my very sensitive neck. It is very loud, unfortunately, and cleaning it didn't seem to make a difference. Trims my head fine with and without the guide combs, too; It never got stuck or bogged down in long hair and the turbo button makes it even smoother. The smaller detail trimmer provides a great pre-shave trim, but it is probably not going to make sensitive skin very happy because it doesn't have a guard. The detail foil shaver is the tiniest one I have ever seen, and is absolutely worthless. Extremely loud, extremely uncomfortable, and it barely cuts anything on your neck unless you go over a spot 20 times. The cone attachment is pretty good for the nose, but for nothing else unlike advertised, of course. Actually if careful, the foil shaver is good for around the eyebrows. Long nose hairs may be pulled, though, so this is to be used semi-regularly.

It also comes with a small brush and a tray to hold everything, but it looks and feels like a part of the packaging, very dumb. Definitely something to shove in the back of the bathroom cupboard or to get rid of altogether.

I would only recommend this for the primary cutting head, but this is hardly the best value. Just get something better like I am about to do.

column13: BEWARE OF ORGANIC IN THE TITLE OF THIS PRODUCT!!!!
column14: Consumers should always be aware of organic in the title.You only need one or two ingredients in body care products in the United States to use organic in your title. Also be very suspicious when you look at a product on Amazon and there isn't any ingredients listed on the page or label of the product. Last when there is a long list of ingredients in a body care product you can bet that most of the time it isn't really organic. Also know the harmful chemicals that they try and hide under the title of organic in their long list of ingredients. In this product they do not list any of their ingredients on the Amazon page. column14:
I've had this for over a year, and I'm just now writing the review. I use it daily and sometimes twice a day and it still works fine. A few times a week, I'll dilute mouthwash, such as Closys in it for a little more periodontal disease reducing punch. It comes with different attachments but I find the regular attachment is best for me. There is an ortho attachment but that one is to refined for my level of sensitivity. I think mine has lasted so long because I put the canister upside down to dry after each use.
If you're new to water picking, I recommend starting on the lowest setting for the few times before going up. Especially if you have diseased gums. I has some bleeding the first few times but that went away. With continued use, my oral health has been much better and I'm getting cavities at a much slower rate than I've had in the past.

column6: HQRP Battery for Philips Norelco 6863XL 6865XL 6866XL 6867XL 6885XL 6886XL HQ8885 Razor / Shaver plus Screwdriver and Coaster
column14:
In service one month thus far. Batteries charged in under an hour and are holding the charge for the expected period. May it so continue.

The previous replacement batteries, from another supplier, after just two years could no longer hold a charge; correct charging and use practices were followed. Those batteries indicate 600mAh 1.2V, while these indicate 700mAh 2.4V. Perhaps the prior batteries were incorrect, but just like the current batteries they were ordered through Amazon for the same shaver model.

As explained in other reviews, the first time replacement batteries are installed the original batteries have to be cut out, being careful to leave the metal contact tabs and using paper shims to ensure the tabs stay in contact with the terminals of the replaced batteries. Subsequently, the old battery pack comes out and a new one is installed just as in any replaceable battery device. The HQRP supplied square socket screwdriver is nice but not necessary, previously a jeweler's straight blade screwdriver was adequate.

It really is poor form for Philips/Norelco to not have designed this shaver for the easy use of replacement batteries, and yet to expect the consumer to extract the battery pack before throwing away the otherwise usable shaver.

column13: Finally, a mascara that doesn't clump or smudge
column14:
This is the first time I've tried this product and I'm very pleased with it so far. This mascara is waterproof, so now I can go swimming without looking like I have two black eyes when I get out of the water!

More importantly though, this mascara really defines and makes my eyelashes look much more think than the Cover Girl mascara I was using before. Not only that, but I would always get clumps and smudges to try to fix when applying my old mascara and haven't had those issues with this one, and the black color matches my lashes perfectly.

I start at the very base, and wiggle the brush back and forth a few times to build up volume, then slowly move the wand up and backwards, to create a curl. After that I brush my lashes from the top as well so the mascara looks thicker, and then use the tip of the brush pointed vertically to dab some on the the lashes at the outer corners of my eyes and I'm done. I've been using Jojoba Oil to remove my makeup, so I tried it to remove this mascara and it worked as well as it did for my former mascara so I'm pleased.

When using this mascara I found that it lasted all day without irritating me, and doesn't flake, smudge, or wash off in my pool.

Retail sample was provided at no cost for evaluation and review purposes.

column6: Pleasingcare Silicone Sonic Facial Cleansing Brush, Rechargeable Face Cleaning Electric Brush, Safe Natural Skin Care Machine
column14:
I have never tried a sonic face cleaner before so all of this was a new experience. I've had facials in a salon before but that was ages ago. This is really very simple to use. I took it out of the box and plugged it into charge. Once it was done I put my facial soap on my face and started scrubbing my face with this. I wasn't sure it was actually doing anything but it did feel like a great facial massage. After cleaning, I washed the soap off of my face and moved on to my toner. I was surprised at how little the toner had to take out. I work in an auto shop and so my face is constantly dirty. This really did the trick on getting the dirt out of my pores. My face felt so much softer after using this and I will continue to use it. I like that it is rechargeable and so there is no need to stock up on batteries.

I only gave it 4 stars for two reasons:

1) The instructions are written so absolutely tiny that I had to get a magnifying glass to read them. The instructions need to be larger because not everyone will have a magnifying glass handy.

2) There is no cover for the charging port. You have to rinse this off after you use it and I was extremely careful not to get water anywhere near it. I would suggest that there needs to be some sort of plug that can be put in to protect that portion.

This really is a great tool and I will continue to use it.

I received this free in exchange for my honest opinion.

column13: tested in sticky, steam August in New Orleans, passed w/ flying colors! 5+
column14: I am both shocked and pleased at how well it works! I expected to be like all the other natural deodorants I've tried over the years (there are a handful of mostly unused natural deodorants that I've given up on at any given time in my bathroom), but this one is definitely different. There's no odor, not even by the time I'm stepping back into the shower again. It's incredible! I am totally throwing out all of the others I've experimented with. I want to reiterate a few things other reviews pointed out, because I read through most of them before I purchased (ultimately, that's why I decided to try it, I decided that many people couldn't be promoting a product that didn't really work.) Definitely less is more in application. On my first day, I think I applied too much, and my skin got a mild rash. I have severe allergies and sensitive skin, so I just need to be careful, I imagine most people won't have to deal with this. For me, applying less = no rash + all day and night protection. Also, I did receive an email request from the company to leave a review (in addition to requests from many other companies items I purchased in that order — it's not just this company that asks for feedback.) It said, "We are a small business, and reviews mean the world to us.  We would like to thank you for being a customer!" and "Are you not 100% happy with your purchase?  Do you have any questions, comments or feedback?  Please email us and let us know!  Our goal at Green Tidings is for our customers to be happy, and to resolve any issues you may have!" This is a company that appreciates business, wants a chance to make things right if a customer is unhappy, and values input from customers in general. As a consumer, this is the kind of communication and care from a company that I want my hard earned money to support.
