column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: Fantastic Top of the Line Electric Shaver
column14:
I received this product as part of a promotion from BzzAgent.

The Braun 9090 electric shaver is a fantastic product, and I couldn’t be happier.

I have a full, coarse and tough beard like razor wire, but also have very sensitive skin and am prone to ingrown hairs. I’ve owned and used numerous top of the line electric shavers from Braun, Panasonic and Norelco, cartridge razors like the Gillette Fusion Proglide and Mach 3 Turbo, and even old fashioned double-edge razors used shaving brushes and soap. I’ve found that foil electric shavers offer me the best shave with the least irritation, and before the Braun 9090, my preferred shaver was Braun’s prior top model, the 790. I intended to purchase a new Braun Series 9 regardless of the promotion, and was excited to try the shaver immediately upon its release.

The Braun 9090 came well-packaged, was easy to open, and included the shaver, cleaning unit, power cord, one Clean & Charge cartridge, a reinforced cloth travel case, cleaning brush, and instruction manual.

The shaver is made in Germany, has a matte gray plastic front and black rubber back, is very ergonomic and comfortable to hold, and light, but solidly built. The cleaning unit is sleek, and far more stylish than old style cleaning units used with Braun’s Series 7 and other models.

I’ve now used the shaver for about a week, and without a doubt, it’s the smoothest, fastest, and most comfortable and irritation-free shave I’ve ever experienced. Despite the four cutting elements on the relatively large shaver head, I had no trouble navigating my neck, jawline or under my nose, and the shaving head’s improvements over my trusty Braun 790 permitted a clean shave without having to go over certain spots repeatedly because the whiskers grow in different directions. It was also far better with multi-day growth than the 790. The shaver was louder than most rotary electrics, but a little quieter than my old Brauns and Panasonics. I prefer to use a pre-shave powder (Remington Face Saver) when using an electric shaver, but achieved nearly equal results with William’s Lectric Shave or without any prep product.

My only complaint was the pop-up trimmer. Most electric shavers include such trimmers, and they usually are barely adequate. However, the Braun 9090’s was worse than most, and notably inferior to the Braun 790. The trimmer pops-up flush to the back of the shaving head, and as a result, it’s difficult to maneuver and see what you’re cutting. It’s also inexplicably slightly concave, and effectively reduces the cutting area and precision.

The Braun cleaning unit is unquestionably the best in the market. It’s fast, truly disinfects with an alcohol-based cleaning solution, efficiently dries the shaver, and is not too loud. The shaver is usually cleaned, lubricated and dry within approximately 45 minutes. Unlike my Braun 790’s cleaning unit, the 9090’s uses a fan a part of the drying process, and is therefore a little louder. If you don’t want to use the cleaning unit or are traveling, the shaver is totally waterproof, and can be easily cleaned under the tap, with or without soap. It’s also possible to simply tap out the hair from the shaving head and brush-out the whiskers. If you manually clean the shaver, Braun recommends that you occasionally oil the shaving head and trimmer. Unlike my prior Brauns, the manufacturer did not include a small bottle of oil, although Braun sells its own oil separately, or you can use the spay cleaners from companies like Remington (Shaver Saver).

I would highly recommend the Braun 9090 to anyone looking for great shave comparable to a blade. However, I offer two caveats. First, although excellent, the Braun Series 9 shavers are expensive. The Braun Series 7 shavers will provide a great shave nearly equal to the Series 9 at a lower price. If budget is a factor, the Series 7 is a better value, but if you want the best of the best, do not hesitate to choose a Series 9. Second, unlike other top models from Norelco and Panasonic, the Braun 9090 is only a dry shaver, and even though it is waterproof, it cannot be used to shave wet, in the shower, or with foam or gel. If I had purchased a Series 9, absent a very high price premium, I would have definitely chosen one of the Series 9 models that could be used wet, such as the Braun 9095.

Summary:

Pros:
+ Smooth, comfortable shave!!!
+ Ergonomic, easy to hold, non-slippery handle
+ Efficient cleaning-unit with an alcohol-based cleaning solution that is widely available
+ Waterproof for manual cleaning
+ Long battery life (50+ minutes, 5 minute quick-charge, and can be used while plugged-in)
+ Good protective travel case
+ High-quality, made in Germany

Cons:
- Expensive (but not unreasonable for a top of the line electric shaver)
- Ineffective and difficult to use pop-up trimmer
- Lubricating oil for manual cleaning not included
- Cannot be used wet and/or with shave foams or gelss 7 is a better value, but if you want the best of the best, do not hesitate to choose a Series 9. Second, unlike other top models from Norelco and Panasonic, the Braun 9090 is only a dry shaver, and even though it is waterproof, it cannot be used to shave wet, in the shower, or with foam or gel. If I had purchased a Series 9, absent a very high price premium, I would have definitely chosen one of the Series 9 models that could be used wet, such as the Braun 9095.

Summary:

Pros:
+ Smooth, comfortable shave!!!
+ Ergonomic, easy to hold, non-slippery handle
+ Efficient cleaning-unit with an alcohol-based cleaning solution that is widely available
+ Waterproof for manual cleaning
+ Long battery life (50+ minutes, 5 minute quick-charge, and can be used while plugged-in)
+ Good protective travel case
+ High-quality, made in Germany

Cons:
- Expensive (but not unreasonable for a top of the line electric shaver)
- Ineffective and difficult to use pop-up trimmer
- Lubricating oil for manual cleaning not included
- Cannot be used wet and/or with shave foams or gels

column6: Murad Sensitive Skin Soothing Serum, Redness Therapy, 1 fl oz
column14:
Truly amazing. I have redness on my cheeks and nose due to sun damage and broken capillaries under the skin, and it can be unattractive and embarrassing. When I blush or exercise, I turn even more red, and people have told me I look like a tomato.

Not anymore! I started using this product about a week ago and I've already seen results. It's gradually diminishing my redness and evening my skin tone. My skin is sensitive and this is one of the only products that not only doesn't irritate my skin, but also soothes preexisting irritation, and protects against further sensitivity.

In the morning and at night, after cleansing and toning, I massage about two squirts of the serum into my face, concentrating more product on areas with redness. This stuff is hydrating, but I need some extra moisture afterwards. It's lightweight, but a little sticky after applying, so I like to wait a few minutes for it to absorb into my skin before I add Clinique's Moisture Surge on top. If I'm in a pinch I just mix both products on my hand and they blend nicely, as they are both gel based.

I'm very impressed and excited to have already seen results, as it has only been a week, and it seems like the bottle will last me a long time. I highly recommend this product.

column6: Seurat Grand Jatte Afternoon in the Park Tote Bag
column14:
Seurat is my favorite artist of all time, and "La Grand Jatte" is my favorite of his paintings. So when I saw a girl on the subway wearing this bag, I had to ask her where she got it. I was so surprised and relieved to find out that it was from Amazon, a company I trust and can use easily.

I've been using this tote for several months now. It's very sturdy, and holds a LOT without being too big to carry conveniently--SO worth it for the low price. The design on the bag is beautiful, very detailed with vivid colors. You can actually see the individual pointillist dots from the original painting--wow. Every single time I wear it out I get a compliment on it, or somebody asks me where they can find it. So happy to tell them they can get it here. Such a perfect addition to my closet, thank you Amazon!

When I use it I feel like I'm in a spa. I am going on a long flight soon so I definitely plan to bring this as I think it would be perfect for travel. It feels pretty lightweight so it will fit perfectly in a carry on bag. This will also be great for traveling because it is so soothing it can relieve the stress of traveling. column6: Unforgivable Eau de Toilette for Men by Sean John
column13: Why did they reformulate the original and weaken it?
column14:
Through no fault of the seller, this is not the original formula of Sean John cologne. As others mentioned, when Sean Combs' company stopped selling this, another company bought it and obviously found a way to produce it cheaper. (more alcohol, less fragrance) which means the scent lasts much less time than the original. The funny thing is, when Sean Combs launched this scent many cologne enthusiasts knew right from the first smell that his company had pretty much copied a scent from Creed, the expensive French perfumery. Creed's version of this scent has been around for ages and cost over $300 per bottle. Sean John Unforgivable debuted at $60 per bottle. (with a limited edition higher concentrated scent which lasted for a day called Sean John Unforgivable at $120/smaller bottle) Needless to say, Creed was not happy about Sean John's almost identical scent selling for much less.

I used to wear the Multi-Platinum limited edition because it lasted so long ... but after my stockpile ran out, I began to order it on websites only to find it was counterfeit. I figured at the least, I could get the regular version of Unforgivable which was usually good for 4-5 hours or more when made by Combs' company. When I purchased a bottle, I was immediately aware that it was much weaker smelling than before. I was further disappointed to note I was lucky to get 30 minutes to an hour of lasting time on the scent. I am not sure why these perfumers cut the scent this much. I can't imagine anyone ... even anyone who loved the scent ... would buy such a weak concentration that lasts such a short time. Upon doing research, I learned that Sean John stopped making the scent under their brand and licensed it out to a different company who changed the formula.

This is a shame because it was a nice fresh scent which smelled like Italian citrus and cola. It was also nice to wear a similar scent to a $350 Creed offering and pay much less. Alas, I won't be buying any more because the scent just does not last.

column6: Rimmel Scandaleyes Waterproof Gel Eyeliner, 0.1 Fluid Ounce
column14:
I purchased this eyeliner as part of a summer long quest to find the perfect waterproof liner. I normally use L'Oreal's Infallible Lacquer Liner 24H, which is a gel liner, so I was excited to try this particular liner. I like gel liners because I find that I get more precision and control out of them than pencil or liquid liners. Some other reviewers have noted that the brush was bad, the brush is pretty typical of those that come with other gel liners I've tried, but it is somewhat lacking in quality so I just switched it out for one of my other liner brushes.

The Good: It is waterproof! I tested it out on my hand, let it dry for a few minutes, then ran water over my hand. It didn't run. Then I tried gently rubbing it with my finger, it didn't smudge or flake. I actually had to rub pretty hard at the back of my hand with makeup remover to get it off, which was very impressive.

The Bad: compared to my L'Oreal gel liner this one did not go on very smoothly. Ultimately it wasn't bad, but it did take more work on my part to get it smooth and even.

Overall I would recommend this product if you like gel liners and you want one that is affordable and waterproof. However, if you just want a long lasting gel liner I'd recommend L'Oreal's.

I was lucky enough to try this product for free from Crest and BzzAgent. Based on the price, I don't believe that I would have purchased it to try on my own otherwise.

The first step in the two part system, the toothpaste comes with a warning that the fluoride may cause staining. Right off the bat, that seems counterproductive. The chemicals used to flavor and sweeten this toothpaste leave a slightly unpleasant aftertaste in your mouth for quite a while. Step one has a very gritty texture, but none of the tiny plastic beads that tend to get caught under the gums causing irritation. After brushing for one minute with the Step One toothpaste I have noticed that my mouth feels very strange. Sort of numb and tingly, parched and dry feeling.

The second step is a peroxide sort of gel. After brushing with Step One you are supposed to spit, and start Step Two right away. I had no problems with the second step, there was no bleaching of my gums or insides of my cheeks. I experienced no increased sensitivity even after a week or more of use. I do find myself wondering if I could just mix step one and step two in order to save time,

I took before and after pictures at the same time of the day in the same location after two weeks of use and I am sorry to say that I did not noticed any difference in the whiteness of my teeth.

column6: Lipogaine for Men Intensive Treatment and Complete Solution for Hair Loss/Thinning, 2 oz
column14:
In 2012, I started using various products containing minoxidil to deal with thinning hair. It was most noticeable in the crown area, but also thinning elsewhere. I've used Rogaine Foam, Spectral DNC and Lipogaine. Lipogaine comes out the clear winner of the three. All 3 helped re-grow hair, but only Lipogaine did this without unwanted side-effects: Lipogaine does not smell bad (like Spectral DNC) nor change the texture of your hair in ways that makes styling difficult (like Rogaine Foam).

Anyone that's starting to use a product containing minoxidil needs to first realize that the process of re-growing hair is long-term. I did not start seeing noticeable results for about 3 months. Again, I emphasize START SEEING RESULTS. You are not going to grow a full head of hair in 3 months - but if you keep at it, the product will work.

One aspect of my thinning hair I don't like is my hairline at the forehead. Although I've read that minoxidil products are not best at working in this area, I have spent several months carefully applying Lipogaine to this area and have seen definite regrowth. Hopefully I will work as well as it has with the rest of my head.

I'm definitely pleased with the results. My head of hair is fuller and the hair is strong. I also like the fact Lipogaine (unlike other minoxidil products) does not have a bad smell and does not create problems with styling my hair.

column6: SKG Handheld Nano Ionic Cool Mist Face Hydration Sprayer - Portable Facial Moisture Instrument
column13: Perfect to slip in my pocket or purse to have a refreshing cool fine mist while outside on a hot summer day!
column14:
[[VIDEOID:7cf497ced382759c9c19c5a3bd596700]]I was really intrigued when I saw this SKG mist sprayer and thought it might be a great product to keep around for the hot, humid summers, so I was excited to give it a try. My first thought when I got this was to be impressed at how small and lightweight this is. It's a perfect size to slip into any of my purses or even my pocket to have it at the ready when I'm on the go. It's nice that it recharges via USB (using the included mini USB cord which is a nice length as well), so that it isn't weighed down by batteries that have to be replaced.

There is a plastic cover on the back of the unit that easily slips off to reveal the water reservoir. It has a plug that is simple to open up and then it can be quickly filled up using the included plastic pipette. The opening is small, so it's best to use the pipette as filling directly from the sink might get a bit messy. The plug fits very tightly in, so that it's totally watertight. I tried closing it up and shaking the whole thing vigorously and not a drop leaked out. Once the unit is charged up and filled with water, it's all ready to go.

To activate the mist, all I need to do is slide open the front cover to reveal the nozzle.
The nozzle sprays out an extremely fine mist, which is great because it cools me off without actively making my skin feel wet. The fineness of the mist also means that it will take a while to go through the water in the reservoir, even though it only holds a small amount. The documentation says that it will spray for 10 minutes, which may not sound like long, but in reality I only use it for a few seconds at a time to cool off, so that should get me plenty of uses on a single fill.

I'm very glad that I was able to order this as a free promotional sample in order to evaluate and provide my honest review.

column6: Temporary Tattoos Metallic Silver Gold - Jewelry Tats - 5 Sheets, 96 Designs
column13: These temporary tattoos are just fabulous!
column14:
I love love LOVE these temporary tattoos!! There is nothing more fun, and they are so easy to use and look fabulous! I love the shiny metallics. I've used a lot of temporary tattoos before but most were just plain black, with very simple designs. These are so far above the norm, they are in a class by themselves. I went to the post office today to buy stamps, and the postal clerk commented on how pretty my "bracelets" are. They are two of the metallic designs from this set of temporary tattoos. I was flattered. :) Then I explained to her what they were and her eyes got big. I don't think she had ever heard of temporary tattoos before.

Real tattoos just aren't for me. They're fine for other people, but I just don't want them personally. But I love temporary tattoos because I can change up my look whenever I want, they are inexpensive, no needles and no pain, plus they go on easily and are removed easily. These last a long time too. I can wear them for several days, even through showers, and they still look sparkly and shiny. If I need to remove them for whatever reason, they come off easily with a little baby oil. The metallic foils are really shiny, and the sunlight catches them and makes them sparkle. It's like jewelry for your body!

column13: Best physical sunscreen by far that I have tried.
column14:
This is so expensive (which is why I gave it four stores rather than five). But it is truly better than any other sunscreen I have tried, and I have tried many. This is a "physical" sunscreen rather than a chemical sunscreen. After reading about the two types I decided that I wanted to use only a physical sunscreen even though they tend to be thicker and less lovely from a cosmetic point of view. They protect just as well and they are felt to be safer, as some of the chemicals used in chemical sunscreens are questionable.

The Clarins sunscreen has a wonderful texture -- amazing slip and goes on so smoothly, but with no feeling of oiliness at all. It is slightly white on your face for a moment, but quickly becomes completely sheer. Once you try this, you're hooked as all the other sunscreens feel so much heavier and greasy by comparison.

I continue to use a really heavy duty screen on my face when I swim laps -- my face is white when I head out to the pool. But for every day the Clarins is what I love the best. Hate paying the price for this, but will have to just scrimp somewhere else.

column6: ToiletTree Products Deluxe LED Fogless Shower Mirror with Squeegee, 1.45 Ounce
column14:
I'm not one for product reviews, really. I read them voraciously, but rarely do I bother to write them.

I've been thrilled with this mirror. I purchased it in December 2014 after reading a glowing review on www.thesweethome.com (and a gazillion of them on Amazon). Amazon delivered quickly, the instructions were straightforward and readable, and I installed it right away. After waiting the recommended 24-hours after install, I took my first shower/shave with this puppy, and it was delightful. It stayed completely fog free, the LEDs did a commendable job of lighting my bearded mug, it held my shaving gear just so, and when a little droplet of water found its way to the reflective surface, I quickly and delightedly wiped that sucker away with the included squeegee. I've used it with joy ever since.

Then, the horror. In my deepest slumber, I heard a horrific racket from the bathroom. Of course I assumed it was an intruder. I grabbed the phone book I keep under my bed for just such intrusions (just kidding), and wandered into the bathroom to identify the source of the commotion. My beloved mirror had fallen from the tile wall and rest sad and broken on the shower floor.

I wept (but just a little), and went back to bed.

Not long after, I shot an email to the company in the hopes they would have some advice for me. Without so much as a question, they immediately offered to send me a new one free of charge and included a silicone remover to get the old goop from the wall.

This review, I guess, is to sing the praises of the mirror first and foremost. But it also aims to sing the praises of the company, which handled my issue quickly, fairly, without question, and with the utmost respect. I have been thrilled from tip to tail.

Just buy the mirror already. It'll change your life in small but meaningful ways. And if it doesn't, rest assured the company will remedy that for you.

column6: Lipogaine for Men Intensive Treatment and Complete Solution for Hair Loss/Thinning, 2 oz
column13: BUT this is a GOOD thing. It is a good indication that the ...
column14: I have used Lipogaine for two years now. I first began using it in July of 2013 and began noticing effects after about three weeks. My hair began to fall out. BUT this is a GOOD thing. It is a good indication that the product is working. Once the follicles are stimulated enough to start regrowing hair, they will push the thinner and dead strand out in favor of a newer thicker strand growing underneath. I'd say after 2 months (looking at before and after pictures) my hair started to regrow. Maximum effect was probably visible after 3 to 4 months. Lipogaine definitely worked to a degree. Its not a solution to hair loss but certainly can regrow hair a little bit and halt further hair loss. The beneficial effects will start to taper off though I think after about a year, which may suggest that cycles of treatment may be the most optimal way to use it.

column6: LAVO Glycolic Toners
column14:
I have keratosis pilaris on my upper arms (little bumps that are benign and don't hurt-- I think something like 1 in 3 people have them, and it's genetic). The only thing that worked for getting rid of these in the past was amlactin lotion (which contains lactic acid). However, the amlactin didn't soak in well and left my skin feeling sticky. I hated this feeling enough that I stopped using amlactin, and instead decided to try a toner that contained an alpha hydroxy acid.

I'm really glad I bought this LAVO glycolic acid toner. It contains 10% glycolic acid, which has been effective on my keratosis pilaris after about a week of twice daily application. Unlike the lotion I was previously using, this leaves my skin feeling silky smooth and clean-- no greasy residue. It stung a tiny bit but only the first two times I used it. After the first few days I noticed dead skin sloughing off whenever I rubbed my arms, and the bumps have cleared up about 70%. I will definitely be repurchasing this toner since it's a good price for such a huge bottle (6 oz), and, because it's thin and runny, a little goes a long way.

The only reason I haven't tried it as a facial toner is because the skin on my face is very sensitive to fragrance, and this product seems to have a strong dose of some kind of fragrance. Don't get me wrong-- it smells very nice, like jasmine and musky white flowers-- but it is stronger than what you might typically find in a facial product.

I was given a discount on this product in exchange for an honest review.

column6: Vitamin C Serum
column13: Cheaper to make it yourself, and surprisingly easy to do
column14:
I didn't get any noticeable results using this serum, and I applied it every day.
The best Vitamin C for your skin is in the form of L-Ascorbic acid. I didn't realize that that was the the best form until doing a lot of research online. That form is pricey, some companies charge upwards of $75 for a 1 oz tube. Once Vitamin C is exposed to air it looses it's potency. Because of this, the ideal way to store the serum is in a pump bottle. Each time you open the Eve Hansen bottle some of the effectiveness is lost.
I've now started making my own toner. I use the Eve Hansen bottle, which is the right color (amber) to make sure minimal light reaches the vitamin (which breaks it down).
I order L-Ascorbic powder from Amazon, along with pH strips. The pH has to be between 3 and 4 to work on the skin. I mix about one tablespoon of distilled water (must be distilled, available at grocery/drug stores for about $1) and less than 1/8 of a teaspoon of the L-Ascorbic powder. I have a pill grinder that I use to grind the powder down super fine, which makes it a lot easier to dissolve. The tonic lasts for about two days, maybe three, although it can be made in larger batches. I make small amounts because of the dropper, which exposes the toner to air.
It can also be made with vegetable glycerin to make a serum.
Making this the way I do costs maybe $20 each year. It works, and works well. Google DIY vitamin C serum and you'll find a ton of recipes and reviews.

column14:
I received the Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing & Whitening system for free - as a promotion for the brand - and my opinion is 100% my own - based on my personal experience using this product.
I am giving this product 3 stars - or an "okay" rating after following the instructions and using the product for 26 days (twice per day).
Here are the reasons I like this product:
1) The instructions are easy to understand
2) The size of the product is enough to last at least 30 days (if used 2 times per day as instructed)
3) The taste - no horrible after-taste - although, I would recommend not eating or drinking right after using the product
4) My teeth actually felt clean & polished - with that "smooth as a dentist polish" feel.
5) I did see improvement in regards to whitening - but only a shade or two - nothing dramatic.
And my reasons for most likely not purchasing this product in the future:
1) The packaging was tough to open. Yes, I could have tried using scissors but I was being lazy. Instead, I opted to try breaking the top corner off - which resulted in a small cut to my finger. The packaging is a hard plastic of sorts.
2) The directions tell you to brush using tube #1 - and NOT to rinse - then to use tube # 2 and brush. Which is pretty simple - however - I could not break the habit of rinsing after brushing. Which may have resulted in me not seeing better whitening results.
3) While my teeth felt clean, I don't feel like my entire mouth/breath was clean after using. In fact, I had to follow up with mouthwash an hour later.

I will most likely not purchase this product in the future.

column6: Infiniti Pro by Conair Tourmaline Ceramic Curling Wand; 1-inch to 1/2-inch; Pink  (packaging may vary)
column13: Fabulous, long-lasting Curls for any look or occasion!
column14:
Throw away curling "irons" or "brushes", rollers, rags, or whatever you use to make curls.

I have hard-to-curl hair that does not hold curls made with other processes, even with mousse, gel, hair spray, etc.

I start with Tressemme Heat protector spray on dried hair. I then use a very small amount of alcohol-free mousse.

Depending on the style of curls I want, I use either a 1/2 inch or a 1 inch section of hair. I wrap it around the wand, hold it there for 10 seconds. BE CAREFUL!! There is no clamp, so you have to hold the edge of the hair close to the wand.

NOTE: test this on an inconspicuous section in the very back - some people have burned their hair right off using too much heat. The wand comes with a half-glove to protect your thumb, forefinger and middle finger, but it takes a bit getting used to.

After curling each section, gently dust the curl with hair spray, from the bottom to the top.

Creates beachy waves, a whole-head of spiral waves, or any other kind of curled look you want. This curling wand (and its thicker cousin), creates curls that lasts days. If I waited 3 days to wash my hair, it would still be curly.

This is my favorite hair appliance, by far.

column14:
This wig is exactly as pictured. It came neatly folded in a plastic bag with care instructions as well as a black mesh wig cap. It's incredibly thick, soft, and full. The cap is adjustable, so it should be able to fit most head sizes (the hooks on the back side of the wig can clasp to the 'ribbon' of sorts that is sewn along each side of the cap's rear), as well as durable. The wig cap comes into immense use if you're someone with long or thick hair (i.e. Me). So far, I can't find any imperfections in the product. I've seen similar quality wigs for easily triple or quadruple the price, so it truly is a steal.

As far as storage goes:
Just make sure that you have a place where you can hang the wig or a wig stand, so that it won't get any difficult gnarles or tangles. Even if the wig is styled to look like Merida's mess of curls, there's always a big difference between an intentionally messy look and an actual birds-nest. Even neatly tucking it back in it's bag should be alright-- just don't leave it lying around somewhere.

I 100% recommend this product for its low price, incredible quality and fast shipping.

column6: Avon Moisture Therapy Intensive Healing & Repair Hand Cream Extra Dry Skin 4.2 Fl Oz. Fragrance Free
column14:
I finally found my hand cream! I have dry and sensitive skin, so finding the “right” moisturizing cream has always been a bit of a challenge… and there are SO many products out there so the search has been overwhelming (and costly). Avon nailed it – this cream is thick (but not gooey) and durable, delivering immediate, moisture therapy and softness for my dry skin. It also outlasts (much longer than the eight hours listed on the package) other creams – the smoothness and hydration delivered immediately upon application survived many, many hand washes and lasts all throughout a night of sleep too. And it only takes a little bit to go a long way, so it’s a great value for the low price.
I also like that this hand cream is fragrance free so I did not have to worry about a scent that irritated me and/or didn’t work for my tastes. It is a nice slim size, so I put it in my handbag and carry with me and also it’s easy to travel with.
Nice job, Avon. Thanks to you my search for the perfect moisturizing cream is over. (My only suggestion to you would be that you are under-marketing the product by labeling it solely as a “hand cream”, because I found it’s great on dry elbows and feet too!)
I will most definitely buy this product again and also plan to buy this for others in my family with dry skin.

column6: Neutrogena Healthy Skin Blush
column14:
I really like this blush "Rosy"/#10. I have fair/medium skin (tan easily) with brunette hair, brown eyes. Blush with a bit of "tawny" color looks best on me. This "Rosy" is a light pink with a hint of tawny/peachy so works perfectly with my skin tone.

It does not come with a brush which is fine with me because I never use those tiny brushes anyway. A little goes a long way & it blends in easily. It lasts most of the day on my skin - longer than most other blush. I had no skin irritation & there is no scent.

The "Bronzed"/#40 color is more of a bronzer than a blush but it looks good blended with the rosy & gives a deeper tawny color if the rosy is too pink for your skin. To use as bronzer apply it before blush to apple of your cheek, forehead, nose & chin - go light or it will look fake & tacky. This is a good bronzer; it's not sparkly. Don't go more than 2 shades darker than your skin or you will look really fake. This one #40 is a medium tone IMO. It might be a tad dark in the deep pale of winter for me.

The "Luminous"/#50 is an illuminating powder; a good one without sparkles. Avoid sparkly - they make you look cheap & fake. You put this on after makeup & blush to illuminate your skin. Apply lightly wherever light hits your skin; cheekbones, temples, forehead, middle of chin & maybe the top of your nose. But if you have oily skin, you may want to avoid this step because it will only make your skin more shiny. Or use only on areas that are not oily. I have an oily t-zone so I only apply this to my cheekbones and temples.

column6: DERMA RESCUE Advanced Ceramide Skin Therapy
column13: Miracle Treatment (but not immediately) but WAY better than shots or ANY other topical!
column14:
I was extremely lucky and grateful to be a part of Derma Rescue's clinical trial in 2014. The product was and is my miracle solution for the horrible psoriasis I have on both feet. The only relief I ever had previously was from painful self-injections into my abdomen. Only one of the many branded prescription injectables had worked and it was unfortunately taken off the market (due to extremely dangerous side effects). Before Derma Rescue, NO topical product had ever worked for me at all.

The only reason I rate it a 4 instead of a 5 is that for me (but not for others, apparently), it takes quite a while before it starts to work. Both during the trial and recently when I restarted it, I was nearly finished with the tube before any positive effects were evident. If I could rate it a 4.7, I would have! That said, by the 2nd and later tubes, it absolutely does the trick—significantly reducing and/or eliminating the itching, scaling, peeling, and even some of the cuts. In my case, however, the redness improves, but never disappears. It is expensive (for me), and there's no insurance coverage for it—don't make the mistake I made of stopping its use. I now had to start all over, when my symptoms completely returned. It is possible that my results take a little longer because of the location of my condition. My psoriasis is on the soles of my feet and they are aggravated constantly. The treated areas can never "relax" since they're covered in shoes (and often socks or pantyhose) and literally walked on every day.

Please feel free to look at the physical proof of my success with Derma Rescue by checking out my before-and-after photos on Kinderma's website in their Before & After Gallery. I took those pictures and they tell the story. I am very much looking forward to trying the new and improved version!

column6: Layouer BB Cream with Peptides, Fruit Extracts + Vitamin A & E – The Ultimate Anti-Wrinkle Beauty Balm –The Secret to a Young and Supple Skin
column13: Makes drug store foundation last almost all day!
column14:
I don't know that I would call this product a BB cream. To me a BB cream moisturizes, is tinted, has anti-aging properties and includes some level of sunscreen. This does mildly moisturize and has some great anti-aging ingredients but it's not tinted and doesn't contain any sunscreen. That doesn't make it a bad product but I use this more as a primer for my inexpensive drug store brand foundations than as a BB cream since it doesn't offer coverage or sun protection.

Once I figured out how I wanted to use it I really started to fins it useful. it absorbs pretty quickly and leaves my skin feeling soft and silky but not with that artificial silicone texture some primers have. I wasn't crazy about the scent of it but once it was absorbed into my skin I couldn't really smell it anymore. However, what I liked the best was that it did a decent job at keeping my very oily skin reasonably oil-free for most of the work day. Although I wouldn't recommend this as a BB cream if you're looking for a solid primer then give this a shot!

Note: I received this product at a discounted rate in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.

column6: Jason 30 oz Revitalizing Citrus Pure Natural Body Wash
column14: I've used regular body washes for years (Nivea, Caress, Softsoap, etc) and was hesitant about switching to a more "natural" body wash, especially in August. SO NOT DISAPPOINTED! It lathers FINE, smells great (light and clean), and the scent lasts about an hour on my skin. I don't care that it doesn't last all day....I already have the scents of my clean clothes, perfume, coconut oil lotion, toothpaste, rinse, deodorant, etc. If you have a particularly bad body-odor issue, this might not be the soap for you. But you shouldn't cover up bad BO anyway - figure out what is causing it. Hyper-hydrosis? Other internal issues? If you eat a lot of onions, that can cause seriously stubborn BO, no matter how strong your external body wash or deodorant is. Or maybe it is red meat? Nothing wrong with meat or onions, but maybe you can eat something else that will fight the internal issue....like parsley or cilantro. But I digress.....Super happy with the purchase, product, and price!

column6: Old Spice Spiffy Mens Sculpting Pomade 2.64 Fl Oz
column13: This pomade was not intended for a slick, greasy look.
column14:
This pomade was not intended for a slick, greasy look. Think more of a "I got a job interview but I want to look like I wash my hair" kind of look. I would say use this pomade for when you want to style your hair as you normally would but in a more reserved "spiffy" fashion. We all have different go to options for a night out vs our 9-5's, right?

The container contains a generous portion of pomade. To my surprise it was white and resembled a paste which isn't really like most pomade products. It really looks more paste like. Texture wise it reminded me of a molding paste that I used manufactured by another company. The pomade itself smelled great and it works great to style your hair.

I attached a picture of my hair with the product. As you can see it isn't greasy but it looks styled and it holds well. Your hair isn't firm feeling but soft and smooth. When applying, be sure to take a dime size portion, rub it vigorously in the palms of your hand and apply it in your hair. I've found that if you want a greasier look with this product it is best to apply it when your hair is wet and comb in.

column13: Original Shirataki Facial Sponge Comes Pre-Moisturized And Helps Clean My Face Better!
column14:
The Original Shirataki Facial Sponge has got to be one of the best facial sponges I've used. I have used a few different facial sponges and mostly the ones that come to you hard as a rock that you have to let sit in water for a little bit before it's ready to go. This facial sponge however comes pre-moisturized and basically ready to go. It does say to soak the sponge in a bowl which I think has to do with excess moisture. I did soak my sponge in warm water for about 5 minutes while I cleaned my face with soap.

I then put a little bit of my cleanser on the sponge and rubbed all over my face. This sponge is extremely gentle on your skin and it has more of a fluff feel to it then anything else. I have sensitive skin so the fact that this sponge didn't bother it at all is amazing. After using this sponge my skin actually felt a lot softer and smoother which I think has to do with the fact that this sponge is a bigger size then what I'm used to so it actually gets every bit of my face without missing anything. I love that it comes with a string so you can hang it up after using to let it air dry. I would definitely recommend the Original Shirataki Facial Sponge!

**I received a discount on this product for testing and reviewing purposes and this is my honest and unbiased opinion**

column13: If you'd like a mast of desiccation and flakiness, this serum is for you!
column14:
I kept getting what I thought was the ~AWESOME PEELING POWERS OF VITAMIN C~ on my face. Then one day, while at work, I barely grazed my chin with my finger and a finger-sized portion of moisturizer/serum just rolled up and fell off my face. What I thought was my skin flaking was actually this serum just SITTING on top of my skin and then flaking/rolling off, taking any and all moisture I put on afterward with it.

I wondered why this serum was just sitting on my face, so I bought some pH strips and, sure enough, the pH of this serum is AT LEAST 9. Vitamin C serum needs to be at most 3.5 in order to penetrate the skin and do its job. This stuff creates a dried up mask on my face. No wonder my skin was so dry while using this.

column14: Biolage Hydro-Foaming Medium Hold Mousse is an excellent product for my fine and hard to deal with hair! I am so glad I found this product. I actually found it at my local grocery store in the beauty and healthcare area, so I didn't need to take a trip to the beauty salon! Over the years I've tried a multitude of products on my hair. One will be too sticky, one will have too powerful of a fragrance, one will have a stuck pump, one will be too heavy, one will make you look like you're using a 1950's hair gel. I've tried so many, but this one I really like. It's lightly fragrant with a very mild scent. I shake then pump a small amount in my hand and apply all over for a total look or just at the ends for curl defining depending on how I want my hair to look that day. It doesn't even feel like I've put it on, yet it really holds my hair. My hair is shiny and moves with my movements, it's not "stuck" from overkill in the styling gel department, yet always maintains my style. The company claims that this mousse protects against heat and thermal styling which is important to me because I always blow dry my hair. I also like that the product has a botanical complex of ingredients. I feel like I am taking good care of my hair. From personal experience I can really recommend this mousse.

column6: Petunia Skincare 5 Piece Set Blackhead Extractor and Acne Remover Kit Specifically Treats Face Blemishes, Pimples, Zits and Whiteheads - Include Giftbox and Travel Case
column13: facial maintenance from a guy's perspective
column14:
I've always had a pimple or two on my face since my teens. They're persistent and at their worst, cringe-worthy---I mean like squirting then gushing pus, and followed by bleeding. Eating MSG and oily foods usually are the main cause of my zits. I think oily skin equals oily, clogged pores. I have been using Biore pore strips for over 10 years now. They work pretty well and keep my face clean, but the strips are pricey. I sometimes can't help but squeeze out blackheads/pimples using my nails in between face washings and pore strips. I recently saw a video featuring a doctor using a "comedone" to extract a patient's blackheads. The video is pretty gruesome to watch. It looked like silly string was coming out of the pores, and the doctor claimed the patient's blackheads were 12 years old! It was nasty but also slightly satisfying to watch. After learning about comedones, I decided to find them on Amazon.

I looked at quite a few and these are the highest (and most) rated. I started using one for the first time yesterday. My goal is to be able to squeeze out clogged pores without leaving scars and without pain. This accomplishes the latter very well and the first fairly well. While these tools aren't painful to use, they do sometimes leave a circular indentation if I press down too hard on my skin, especially my nose. However, though I'm worried about a bit of permanent scarring, this hasn't happened with the comedone. I can say for a fact it has happened before when I used to pinch pimples with my fingertips/nails. I've recently read that you're actually not supposed to use fingers/nails as this causes scarring--instead, the comedone applies even pressure around the pore and doesn't scar. Just keep in mind a good amount of pressure is needed to squeeze impurities out of your pores so this isn't 100% pain free...

The kit comes with a few comedones of various sizes. There's even one with a sharp needle-end. I have no idea what it's for and frankly, am a bit scared--does it pop things? I can see myself using it on a balloon, but my face? Probably not.

The tools are sturdy, yet lightweight and fairly simple to use. I cleaned them off with a cottonball dipped into rubbing alcohol. Instructions are provided on how to use these, but no explanation is really needed--just place device over your zit, exposed in the hole, and push. Black heads/pimples/buildup will come out, and then you scrape it up, taking the impurity with the head of the device.

I'm enjoying cleaning my pores with these. Hope they help you as well.ankly, am a bit scared--does it pop things? I can see myself using it on a balloon, but my face? Probably not.

column6: Secret Outlast Unscented Women's Clear Gel Antiperspirant & Deodorant 2.6 Oz
column14:
I tried Secret Outlast® Clear Gel Deodorant a bit skeptical of what I was going to experience. I don't usually even wear deodorant. I don't participate in any activities that produce a lot of sweat, and I just naturally don't tend to have an odor. However, it being the middle of summer, I figured it was the best time to be trying some out in case I needed it.

The first thing I noticed was that I seemed to have a defective stick that didn't want to expel any of the gel out the top even after relentlessly turning the crank. Eventually some came spitting out and I was able to apply it. It felt so incredibly disgusting when it touched my skin. Very cold and wet, it was so uncomfortable. After flailing around like a maniac with my arms up for a good 5 minutes, it was finally dry enough for me to put on a shirt.

The one thing I can credit Secret with is that I did not end up with white marks on my clothing or my skin. It (much to my surprise) even remained clear with a mild amount of perspiration mixed in. However, as they were advertising odor AND wetness protection, I have to say they missed their mark on the wetness portion. As for odor, I never smelled anything particularly foul coming from me, so I assumed it worked out. I don't know if I'm somewhat desensitized to the scent of the actual deodorant or if it just doesn't smell that strongly, but I didn't ever catch a pleasant aroma, either.

Overall just makes the cut as another average deodorant with nothing super fantastic to note. They did make their promise on it being a truly clear deodorant, but if it's clear yet ineffective in every other way, I don't see much point in buying it.

I tried this product for free as a promotional item through BzzAgent.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Not bad, but not great either
column14:
I am a regular coffee/Red Bull/soda drinker, and I have been using the Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing & Whitening System for several weeks now. Unlike others, I am finding that concerns regarding fluoride staining and peroxide sensitivity are not an issue for me.

I can't really say that consistent use of the product has made my teeth any whiter; rather, I would say that they haven't gotten worse. This leads me to believe that it is a good maintenance product, but not necessarily a good whitening product.

For me, the cost of the system prohibitive - around $25 for toothpaste that frankly won't last more than a month is a lot to spend on toothpaste.

In any event, I was pleased to see that the product did NOT contain any plastic beads that would be harmful to the environment--and my gums. Good on crest for that.

I did receive a sample for review purposes, but I believe that all reviews should provide honest feedback. All opinions expressed are 100% my own.

The flip side is, they leave such a nasty residue on my face I absolutely have to wash my face again to get it feeling clean and fresh. It's a very oily residue on my face and hands.

column14:
This electric manicure tool is great for novice, at home use. It is cordless and comes with 5 attachments and a satin carrying case. It takes 2 AA batteries which are not included. The attachments are easily changeable and offer a variety of uses for shaping, filing, smoothing and buffing during at home manicures and pedicures. I would not compare this to a professional one, but it does the job for my simple needs. It’s speed is enough to get the job done and not fear filing too much nail off.

I would have liked to receive some type of instructions or recommendations on what to use each tool for but there were no instructions included. If you are looking for a simple, easy to use tool for personal use at home, I would recommend this product. I was glad to be able to receive this product at a reduction in price for the purpose of testing, for an honest and unbiased review.

column14: EDIT: After writing my review, the seller contacted me and took care of me! They informed me that they would work on improving the grammar for the instructions.  I've still been using mine, especially the short brush to wash my face every night.      ORIGINAL POST: [[[This item is definitely a good substitute for the more expensive facial cleansers. I like that I can take this product on the go and that it'll easily fit into my purse for travel.  I did throw away the latex sponge, due to contact with people who are severely allergic to latex.  It was extremely helpful that that sponge was labelled as a latex product.  The batteries do die if left in overnight, so that instruction to remove the batteries for best life is also useful. There are some things that the seller could improve: The instructions are poorly written.  The grammar is low-level, making me ponder if this is a foreign product, as it seems the instructions were translated into English with Google.  It would also be helpful to have better and clear instructions on what/where to use the different heads.  For example, after soaking your feet in a warm bath, use the pumice head to get rid of calluses and dead skin. Follow up with the soft brush to brush off the remaining remnants of dead skin. Where the head attaches to the body, mine is beginning to smell like an overrun motor.  I've been giving it a rest to see it that help it.  Additionally, the massaging head does not connect completely, and it falls off a lot.  All in all, it is a good start to an affordable way to have a deep clean for your face washing routine, with added extra heads for bonus! However, I would probably not repurchase.  If you can afford the $30 ones, that would be a better and perhaps safer bet.]]]]

column13: Wonderful! Great quality product and company!

Now the company: due to some unknown mix-up in my order, the mascara did not come in the package I received from Amazon. When I was asked in a a followup email by the company how I liked the mascara, I felt I should tell them that I hadn't actually received the mascara. In less than a week, they were on it, and sent me "another" one for free. You have to like people who do business this way. I hadn't complained because it seemed like a hassle, but they were more interested in me getting the mascara than they were in haggling over where or if the system had broken down. Integrity. It makes a difference.  UPDATE: This is the only mascara I buy! I have recently received my third order, and the quality of the product remains wonderful! column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Bad after taste is just too much for me :(
column14: As soon as I got the campaign invite through BzzAgent to try Crest's new 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing System, I signed up right away. I mean who doesn't want whiter teeth that doesn't cost a fortune?? I was a little intimated by the 2 part system, thinking that it was going to be too time consuming and in the end a product that I would not continue with. However, when I learned what the 2 part process actually was, I realized it’s not bad at all. I tend to brush my teeth for a longer period anyway with my Sonic Care toothbrush, and the 2 step process is quick and simple for me because the toothbrush makes a noise after 1 minute and then stops after 2 minutes. The directions tell you to brush with the Step 1 tube first, which is the Deep Cleansing Toothpaste that prepares your teeth, then spit -don't rinse (which I would tend to forget a time or two)- and then last use the Step 2 tube for the second minute being the Whitening Finisher. The product states the system together is supposed to keep your smile up to 99% as white as a professional polish. There is one big negative in my eyes, and that is the awful after taste that the product leaves in my mouth after brushing, almost making me feel sick. And the taste is still there when I wake up in the middle of the night due to a child crying or bathroom needs, and again it makes me feel sick. I even tried using mouthwash after I brushed but the bad taste still came back. I actually noticed myself after a couple weeks of use reverting back to my old toothpaste here and there to not have to deal with the awful taste. For this reason I will not be purchasing the item in the future. I also noticed that after using the product my mouth felt tingly and parched. It was definitely a weird feeling. As for the whitening results, I have not noticed a significant difference, maybe a slight change if anything. I asked my husband if he noticed a difference and he said "no". So all in all, I was bummed about the productand will continue to use Crest's 3D Whitening toothpaste that I have used for years which I do highly recommend. I also have to say that I read some of the other product reviews and saw the negative comments people were saying about the ingredients in the product which is a little scary and makes me not want to use the product again. I was shocked to see how many other people noticed the bad after taste just like I did! Sorry Crest, but still happy I was able to try it for free :)

column6: 2 PACK of Cure Natural Aqua Gel 250ml - Best selling exfoliator in Japan
column13: Highly Recommended for People who Think Dead Skin Clumps are Cool
column14:
I ordered this product on a friend's recommendation and am very glad I did. Although there is some debate about whether the clumps are skin or the product, I have come down on the side of it being skin for a few reasons. The most compelling reason is that the clumps themselves vary based on where I put the product on my body and whether I've exfoliated that area recently. For example, I put some on the underside of my forearm (a very smooth area) and there was essentially no clumping, while there was quite a bit on the outside of my forearm. I also tested the directions to wash and dry your face before using the product, by putting it on top of my BB cream. Nothing happened at all - no clumping, no exfoliation, nothing, even though I could tell my skin was quite dry. I washed my face, reapplied the Cure Natural Aqua Gel and BAM, dead skin everywhere.

I can also feel a difference immediately. For example, I have dry patches on my arms, as well as on the back of my calf where I cross my legs, and this product has been very helpful in reducing those patches. I use this product on my face about every other day, depending on how my skin feels. I have not found it to be overly drying, as some reviewers have, but I have very oily skin. I love this product and wholeheartedly recommend it.

column14:
I literally read every review on this product and was really hopeful that it would work for me....here are my thoughts...for one it didn't smell at all...some people mentioned an overwhelming sulfur smell...while I did smell the sulfur it was NOT over powering in my opinion...
I have recently started suffering from adult acne per my dermatologist...he injected cortisone in my large cyst like pimples and within a day they were significantly smaller in size...I used this product as a mask... I left in on longer than ten minutes and prior to using it as a mask I used it as a spot treatment over night on the larger pimples I had...Some reviewers reported that overnight the pimple was gone...unfortunately for me that was not the case... they didn't decrease in size at all...Two things I didn't like about the product is that it is very tacky like some reviewers reported...and because of that it didn't stay on my face overnight... I don't know if I should continue to use the product when I haven't seen results...I know everyone's skin is different...maybe it's a time sensitive product and it gradually will work...I'll stick with a little longer...

column14: I fell in love with this fragrance as soon as I smelled it at Macy's, but their price was ludicrous in comparison.  It's a seriously spicy scent that frankly doesn't have much in common with other designer fragrances.  I'd characterize it as having lots of  lavender, cinnamon, tobacco and maybe a bit of sandalwood.  This is the same as Luna Rossa but turned up a notch so I would apply sparingly to avoid overpowering a room.  This is a classy man's fragrance that would likely be suitable for an evening out.  What I like most is that this fragrance steps away from the crowd, so you won't get that feeling of "This smells like..."  It oozes sophistication.  If you're looking for a fragrance that separates itself from the Cool Water and Aqua di Gio crowd, this may be your ticket.

column6: Maybelline New York Superstay Better Skin Foundation, 1 Fluid Ounce
column14:
I was surprised by how thick this foundation was, but happy that it didn't feel heavy or appear thick on my skin. I really like the coverage as it is more sheer than I anticipated. I'm almost 55 years old and still have fairly firm skin with only light wrinkling around the eyes. I had zero issues with my crows feet appearing more pronounced as they have with other foundations. It covered the ever so annoying broken blood vessel on my nose and other various red spots (some type of allergy) on my face all day. I was also in the heat and nothing melted! I have used this color before in other formulations and this type seemed darker. I would suggest mixing with a little water or light moisturizer for the areas around the jawline, under the chin, and neck for blending purposes.

Overall, I recommend this product. Just maybe go a shade lighter than usual.

column13: IT. DOES. WORK. IF. USED. PROPERLY.
column14:
Giving 5 stars for price & results.
I mainly used this to smooth my hair. My hair is thick, naturally wavy & big in the worst places! I followed the instructions. I washed my hair prior to putting the product in, towel dried it a bit then used the entire bottle, waited 20 minutes. then rinsed it out with cool water. column6: Beauty by Earth Natural SPF Sunscreen - All Natural, Mineral & Organic Ingredients - Non-Nano Zinc, Non-Toxic for Whole Family and Reef Safe - Made in the USA
column13: I love it, husband not so much, but it WORKS
column14:
I absolutely loved this sunscreen. I have *very* pale skin, and have been known to get a bad sunburn even during a rainstorm (it's true). This stuff lasted me an entire 6-hour pool party in the middle of July in Texas with only 3 applications (every 2 hours folks!). That's normal to have to reapply, especially when swimming. But with all other sunscreens, and believe me after decades of trying them I have tried them all, I would still get a burn even when re-applying every 1.5 hours.
This sunscreen didn't even let me get a slight burn! I was so happy I literally had tears in my eyes at the end of the day. Yes, literally, not figuratively.

The reason I give 4 stars instead of 3 is my husband hated it. While he too did not receive even a hint of sunburn, it definitely did not soak up into his skin as easily as it went into mine. For me, it was like applying any other sunscreen, if a bit thick. For him, it was difficult to spread it around and had to rub a lot to get it to soak in. It also left his beard looking snowy white where it had gotten into his hair.

column6: GIOVANNI COSMETICS Ultra-Moist Shampoo, Avocado/Olive Oil, 24 Fluid Ounce
column13: but the texture of it is fine & wavy
column14: Giovanni's Avocado & Olive Oil Shampoo is a miracle hair care product beyond compare! I have thick hair, but the texture of it is fine & wavy. It is also very layered & has multiple blond color processes done on it (straight bleach, highlights, lowlights, & tints). I also use a lot of heat. A lot of shampoos--including those for color-treated or over-processed hair--will still leave my hair looking dry, frazzled, & with ends sticking out everywhere. Other conditioning shampoos will weigh my hair down & make it look & feel coated, greasy, & dirty. Ugh. But, Giovanni's Avocado & Olive Oil Shampoo makes my hair smooth (yet full & voluminous), shiny, healthy-looking, vibrant, & clean! While I was waiting for my purchase to arrive (which came within a few days!), I used a different shampoo that was supposedly ultra conditioning & for dry, color-treated hair, but it made my hair look like frizzy straw. It was awful. I thought my hair was ruined beyond repair.  But the minute I washed it with the Giovanni's Avocado & Olive Oil Shampoo, it was smooth, soft, shiny, & voluminous once again! I was so ecstatic. This product is absolutely miraculous. That's really the only accurate way  to describe it. And it seems to work well on all different hair types as well, because my daughter has very thick, healthy, straight, (dyed) black hair with crimson bangs. Completely different hair from mine & she loves this product as well. I also like that this shampoo is essentially scent-free as opposed to the chemical smell or heavily-perfumed scents of most other hair-care products I've tried. In fact, I love everything about this shampoo. You can actually find this shampoo @ Target, but it only comes in a small squeeze tube, which I find inconvenient to use in the shower. I also find it rather difficult to get the shampoo out once you're about 3/4 of the way through the tube. But this economy size available through Amazon with the salon pump makes a great product even better & easier to use. Thanks Amazon!

I have a daughter who is mixed race father is white I am black so her hair is somewhat in the middle . So her hair can get dry very easy. Im not kidding but after washing my daughters hair and conditioning it I used a little bit of this stuff while brushing her hair and this made her hair so so smooth. She is three  years old and when I was done she kept shaking her hair because she loved the feel of it. It's not oily and it smells really good. A little goes a long way so I am expecting this to last me a while. I change products every couple months because the first time I try products it works great but with continued use it doesn't have the same result that it use to have when I first try the products so I stop using them and i move on to something else. I hope this will not be the case with this product. It also made my daughter hair de tangle very easily. Unlike a lot of reviews on here that they received this product at half off or free for a honest review. I paid full price for this item and was not contacted for such a offer. This is my own review and I love this product and recommend others to try it. I will update my review in a couple months.

column14:

I love the pump dispenser because that is more sanitary than digging my hands in a jar daily. The moisturizer comes out easily and just a few pumps is a perfect amount for my entire face.
I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest opinion but the opinion expressed is all mine.

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength 1 Each
column14: Amazing stuff!! After researching all types of colour remover I settled on this one (primarily because it was available at my local drug store). It does stink, no doubt about that, but it's not horrific, and as long as you use a pleasant smelling deep conditioner afterwards your hair should not smell like regurgitated rotten eggs. One disclaimer: my natural colour is dark brown (dyed it blue black for yeaaaars and wanted to return to my natural hair colour) so I'm not sure how this would work with lighter hair. I now kinda wish I had a before and after picture to show you, because I'm still shocked at how well it removed all the black. I originally bought two boxes (based on reviews and the instructions), but only used one - mind you, I'm mixed with unbelievably thick long hair, but I think because this stuff is like water it goes a long way and it REALLY saturated my hair. I would also recommend buying a deep conditioner for after - my hair doesn't  feel/appear damaged, but it's mad dry.   Never thought it would work this well!!!!

My father in law loves this shaver; he can use it dry or in the shower and it has a trimmer attached too. 2015-08-10 US 18126628 R23E78PHJD2JWQ B00O171SJU 923899527 e.l.f. Disney Good vs Evil Beauty Book Day Beauty Night Villian by e.l.f. Cosmetics Beauty 5 5 5 N Y Once upon a dream... I've collected quite a few of these Disney makeup palette's from e.l.f. and they are beautiful, shimmery, and pigmented. I'm a fan of e.l.f. and Disney and love to collect these palettes! If you're not familiar they've made other palettes as well so if you're interested I recommend you research and see how beautiful these palettes are. This Good Vs. Evil palette is currently my favorite. The packaging is gorgeous! It's all black with silver accents of rose thorns and a little dragon on the side. The front shows gorgeous artwork of Aurora and Maleficent among whisps of violet and turquoise dark fairy magic. Inside is a mirror shaped like a rose and if you flip the page it gives you steps to create two unique looks. You can go for an innocent neutral "Day Beauty" look like Aurora or go the opposite for a dark fairy "Night Villian" look like Maleficent.

Day Beauty eyeshadow colors: Sunlight (matte nude, great for blending out), Innocence (shimmery nude, nice highlight), Briar Rose (soft shimmery cotton candy pink, great highlight), Sunbeam (beautiful bronze!), Forest Beauty (shimmery taupe brown, so pretty!), and Woodland (shimmery dark woodsy brown.) These colors are so gorgeous. You also get a mini lipgloss that's very pigmented that's an extremely bright hotpink almost red shade. I love the eyeshadows but not a huge fan of this super bright lipgloss personally.

Vs.

Night Villian eyeshadow colors: Sorcery (shimmery silver), Magic Spell (shimmery turqouise), Evil Fairy (shimmery violet), Hedge of Thorns (shimmery gray), Green Flames (a unique shimmery dark greenish/gray), and Black Magic (a shimmery black.) The lipgloss for this look is much more wearable in my opinion it is quite pigmented as well. It's a dark plummy pink shade I really like it. In this palette you also get one black eyeliner pencil. As far as e.l.f. eyeshadow pencils go I'm not the biggest fan of them. It's great if you've run out of eyeliner and use it as a backup but I prefer to use my better eyeliners. To me e.l.f. eyeliners are a little waxy and smudge too easily.

Overall, this is a beautiful palette and I'd highly recommend it for any female fans of Disney's Sleeping Beauty ages teens to adults. The colors are gorgeous, the packaging is beautiful. Even if you don't use the makeup it's beautiful just to display on your vanity. It doesn't come with any eyeshadow applicator which is fine by me because I don't like to use those anyway. The eyeshadows are shimmery so they can cause a little shimmer fallout on your cheeks but a little magic doesn't hurt once in awhile. column6: real Techniques Starter Set
column14: I ABSOLUTELY LOVE these brushes. I'll splurge on eyeshadow palettes all of the time, but I can't stand dropping more than 10 bucks on a single brush. So, when I came across this kit, I was skeptical yet intrigued. It visually stood out to me from other brushes that quite frankly, looked a little cheap. The bristles are dense yet soft, and even though they DO pick up product well, I didn't find the application amount to be satisfactory for me. However, you can use a cheap eyeshadow brush and it's fine. However, it is undebatable that the brushes distribute the shadow perfectly and evenly. Usually when I blend, I find that the bristles will pick up some color and then deposit it elsewhere, so I really have to work the brush to not have a spotty crease color. This is pretty much why I bought the set; watching tutorials online, I noticed that most women use a soft domed brush for blending. Yup! The base shadow brush has become my crease's best friend. The great thing is that there is a variety of brushes; it's not like some kits where you get several that look very similar and are just different sizes. If you are even considering buying brushes, I'd get these. The great thing, especially if you are a "starter", is that there is a website by the designer with tutorials, so you can learn how to do makeup with the very brushes you own. I wish I had that luxury in the beginning. Also, doing the crease/outer v is typically hard for beginners, and you'll be able to do it like a pro with these brushes. I've gotten good at it on brushes that take me so much longer to do it. This has literally cut my application time in half. I hope you enjoy these, and that this is helpful, especially since I know I'm rambling.

column6: Garnier Hair Color Nutrisse Nourishing Color Creme
column13: 'Ash' means blue in the hair world!
column14:
I see bad reviews all the time for this color because "my hair looks blue!" And people seemed shocked.. I just want to roll my eyes. Ash tones have a blue, sometimes green, tone to them. Really I would call this color a light blue black instead of ash brown but I don't name the colors. If you are going from a naturally light hair color, especially one with ash tones, you will get a more blue effect. And yes it will be dark. I would compare this color to the "natural black" shades of hair color, but with an ash (blue) undertone instead.

That being said, I love this color. Don't shy away from it just because it relieves poor reviews from people who are not educated on color tones. Personally, I love the blue undertones it gives without being full on blue black. I have naturally black hair (not blue/ash...) and this give me a gorgeous color every time. By far my fave. My one complaint os it fades quicker than I'd like and is getting harder to find in store. Not sure if it has been discontinued..

column6: PILATEN blackhead remover,Tearing style Deep Cleansing purifying peel off the Black head,acne treatment,black mud face mask 60g
column13: Skin soft and smooth, but hardly removes blackheads
column14:
Unfortunately, the provided "translated" directions don't work as well as the method other viewers have suggested. I take a warm to mildly hot shower to exfoliate my face, using an appropriate facial cleanser. I then dry my face and liberally apply the black goo across my face, making sure to get around the creases of my nose. Keep it out of your eyes and off your eye brows. I let it dry for 20 minutes, speeding it up by sitting in front of a fan. I then apply a second layer over the now mostly dry top layer. If you apply the second layer on a wet layer, you'll just pull at the still wet "base". I then wait 30-40 minutes, again sitting in front of a fan.

When appropriately dry, the mask is really easy to slowly pull off. I start from the chin and work my way up. I have sensitive skin and I find no problems with this mask. Of course, I also use a sensitive facial cleanser as a routine. The mask leaves my face soft and smooth, but it hardly works well at removing blackheads. Any left over black goo that didn't peel off will easily come off with water and a little bit of soap. I have especially prominent blackheads around my nose. This product hardly touched any of them. I find better use with the conventional white blackhead remover strips that I can find at a local convenience store. This product was nice to try out, but I probably won't use it again.

column6: Best Pre-Shave Oil For Men - Experience The Best Shave Ever With The Best Pre-Shave Oil And Shaving Oil By UrbanXY For Men. BIG 2oz VALUE SIZE!
column14:
My husband trims his beard though out the week keeping a light stubble but on the weekends he gets a clean shave. So as you can understand a week old beard needs some extra care to get a clean shave, which means he always uses a pre-shave treatment. He has a specific cream which he use and he says a little is enough to soften his beard.
When he tried this pre-shave oil, he said that his beard was soft but not as much as his regular cream, but the fact that the oil is pretty moisturizing gets a plus point. The oils has a very light scent to it, not at all over powering.
My husband applied it on his beard and kept it on for a minute or so, so that it gets absorbed properly and then he applied the shaving cream and shaved. The shave was a close one, but he got a pull here and there on his beard and he had to change his blade. Overall a good oil and if you have not used any kind of pre shave treatment before you will like it very much.
**I received the product as a promotional offer in-exchange of my unbiased review.

column13: NEW formula -NOT good. I want the OLD back!
column14: On 1/1/13 - I buy a replacement bottle of this great lotion. IT HAS BEEN CHANGED!! Front says "Smoothing" "now richer formula" - and "with cocoa butter and shea" and a new graphic. NEW?? Oh! NO!! NOT my favorite lotion!! I read the label: WELL, the cocoa butter and shea have moved DOWN on the ingredient list [meaning LESS of those items]. The OLD product was called "Cocoa Butter with shea body lotion". The new product is PEE-weW! stinky- it now has a sicky sweet almost floral fragrance. The old product smelled like cocoa butter - a light pleasant chocolate scent. I ran to Walmart  - and bought EVERY bottle of the OLD product, alas only 3 left. The rest were the "new". I will search long for the OLD lotion! My star rating is for the OLD lotion -5 stars! If I were to rate the new one ...ZERO....as soon as I run out of the old, and can't find more - I will be searching for a different lotion. The graphic on some Amazon listings are the old graphic, BEWARE - but will the lotion be the old product??? The NEW formula has "Smoothing" on the front label -AVOID this. Ask before you buy!!!

column14:
I have been reading a lot about argan oil and how it is produced in Morrocco. The nuts are shelled by hand and then they are cold pressed, also by hand. This is why so many products that claim they have argan oil in have very small amounts. I've been looking for pure argan oil and decided on this brand because I have a vitamin c serum from them that I love.
The uses for this are unlimited really. It can be used as moisturizer, cuticle oil for nail growth, fixing cracked heals, frizz control and split end moisturizer. I have put a few drops into my rose water toner and moisturize that way. When I remove my nail polish I put it on my nails to rejuvenate them after the remover and polish. This is a really good brand, so I feel confident that argan oil is pure. It has worked very well for me and it's one of my favorite products in my beauty regimen. I was lucky enough to purchase this product at discount so that I could provide my honest opinion. I will definitely buy more when I run out.

column6: Dr. Jart Rejuvenating Beauty Balm, Silver Label, 1.7 Ounce
column14: I have oily skin that tends to reject practically every foundation or by cream. By the end of the day, I usually only have half to a quarter of the product still on my face. I have tried one Dr. Jart+ bb cream from Sephora in the past, but I didn't want to commit to that price. That being said, this bb cream is the best bb cream I have ever tried! It is a thicker formulation that really blends into the skin and produces a full coverage. Though it goes on with a gray undertone, it turns into a more natural shade in about 5 minutes. This bb cream will truly give you full coverage with either your fingers or a sponge. The formulation is a bit thick compared to other creams on the market, but a little goes a long way. This product also helped matify my face and gave it sun protection with the built in sunscreen. The final high point was its staying power. It stood up to a full day of running around doing errands and going to a water park. Yes, a water park. By the end of my 3 hours at the water park I had only a quarter of the product come off. I didn't have my head completely submerged a lot, but the bb cream stood up to water jets, sprays, and water slides. Overall, this product is highly worth your money and I can't recommend it enough!

This shampoo cleaned my  hair sufficiently and didn't seem to leave behind any feeling of residue or heaviness on my hair.  It lathers nicely.  I really didn't notice any minty aroma or feel to it.  It does seem to strip the hair clean of build up...which in turn tends to tangle my hair.  The companion conditioner was used, as recommended, and it didn't really smooth out or detangle quite to the degree I'd like.  I have been using a product sold on TV by that famous hairdresser in Los Angeles that is all the rage because it's soap free.  His product leaves my hair totally silky, totally tangle free and is also supposed to remove all harmful residues.  However, it hasn't helped my seborrheic dermatitis and that was my goal with this shampoo/conditioner along with other products to treat it.  What I may wind up doing is continuing down the path with the organic shampoo and using the tried and true tv product as my conditioner because I know it gets the job done.

column13: I Didn't Realize How Great This Shampoo Is...
column14:
until I purchased another product.

I don't normally spend a lot of money on shampoos even though my hair is not in great health. Still, when I realized that I needed to invest in a better shampoo, after doing research, I came across this product. I used the entire contents of the bottle and was pleased with the results; however, the cost of the shampoo made me hesitant to purchase again so I tried a lesser expensive brand. The damage that brand did to my hair was shocking. It left my hair in knots that I had to cut off because they wouldn't comb out...even with a detangler. Needless to say, I re-purchased this shampoo to try to correct the damage that had occurred and much to my surprise (and delight), it not only achieved that goal but exceeded it by restoring my hair (though shorter) to its state prior to the other shampoo. I truly didn't realize how well this shampoo worked but am glad I spent the extra money to purchase it again.

Also, the fact that some of the proceeds goes to St. Jude Children's Hospital is a plus and makes it all worthwhile.
