column6: Fogless Shower Mirror
column13: My Review of the Negative Reviews
column14: I have owned this product for more than one year.  I want to respond to the few negative reviews I  have read about it:  First - at least for the way mine was built when I bought it - It is true that the silicone paste supplied is inadequate, and mine fell off the shower wall the first day I put it up too.  A  quick trip to Home Depot for a large replacement tube solved that problem permanently.  Second - It would indeed be nice if the tray for storing things had a ridge to keep things like one's razor from falling off occasionally.  All else is good:  The mirror has not gotten foggy to this day.  It remains as clear as it was on the first day. The guy who claimed that the squeegee scratched the mirror must have slipped in a razor blade - mine remains perfect. The guy who said he could not properly manage the squeegee because of his "man hands" should check whether his fingers curl and his thumb is prehensile. The few people who said that the plastic spokes to tilt the mirror position gave way in a few months and the mirror then just hung down:  Have you been clicking it into different positions all the time?  Most people would just pick their mirror position and then leave it there.  The thing is made of plastic for gosh sakes (although it is quite hardy).  Mine still stays in place like a rock.  I have never written a product review before, but this just kept nagging at me.  Hope it helps.

I'm 20yo and I have very sensitive and acne-prone skin.
I've been trying to find the perfect lotion/gel/moisturizer since i was around 13yr old and i still haven't found it. I was hoping this would hit home run but it only made it to first base.

What its like on your face:
The product smells amazing imo and it looks really cool. Its a bouncy gel and is completely clear.
Its really really light on your face (WHICH I LOVE) and it keeps the oil at bay for around 3-5 hours for me depending on if I'm wearing makeup or not.
It leaves a cooling sensation on your face (also love) and spreads really easily. It takes a while to dry but i don't really mind that.
Its great before makeup because it doesn't mess with what you're gonna put on your face at all because it dries really well.

After using it for 2 months:
My face feels hydrated but not oily.
Some redness has improved but it hasn't helped with breakouts whatsoever.
Doesn't really work for me as a spot treatment like it does for some people.

Overall:
I love the price for the amount of product you get. Its amazing and i may repurchase on that fact alone.
It doesn't leave my skin feeling sticky or greasy.
Doesn't help acne but doesn't make it worse either.
Good hydration without being heavy and oily.
Keeps oil at bay for how long i need it to (3-5hr)
The smell may be to much for some people but i really like it.
Comes in a jar which some people may find unsanitary.

column6: Nizoral Anti-Dandruff Shampoo
column14:
I'd stopped using Nizoral years ago. Though I was only in my 30s and very healthy, I noticed that when I was regularly using this product I experienced a dull but nagging chest pain. As soon as I stopped, the pain went away.

Fast forward a decade. I decided to try Nizoral again. After using it three times, there was the pain again. I quit for a week. The pain went away. I tried it again. The pain returned.

Yes, this is anecdotal, and yes, this may be limited to only me. Perhaps it's not even related to this product. But it has me concerned enough, that I'll not be using the product again.

column14: I've used plenty of whitening products, but they all make my front teeth super sensitive.  I have two boxes of different types of white strips collecting dust in my medicine cabinet because they make my teeth so sensitive they feel "see-through".  This gives me control over where to aggressively brush and where to leave be (i.e. bottom of front teeth) which white-strips cannot do.  The Step 2 (polish) can irritate the gums at first (I only used it every other day in the beginning until my gums were acclimated to being stimulated more than usual).  My teeth, and my husband's teeth have not been whiter since long ago!  Keeps the coffee stains at bay, too.  The only negative is the taste, but if you follow up with a good strengthening mouthwash, it goes away.  Totally worth it.  FYI I'm trying the product for free thanks to Crest® but my opinions are honest and my own.

column6: SleepRight Dura-Comfort Dental Guard
column13: It gave me dental problems because the silicone that keeps ...
column14: It gave me dental problems because the silicone that keeps your teeth separated idoes not continue to separate all teeth.  It only separates the teeth at either end of the mouth.  Not separating all teeth created an uneven bite, and over a period of three or four years grinding the underside of my bridge damaged my lower teeth and walso ended up exposing more root nerves. That created pain.  My dentist told me that instead of the hard dental nightguard I could use the Doctor's Night Guard Advanced Comfort brand of night guard sold in drug stores. It is actually quite easy to fit, and since the inside is soft it does not give me a headache from grinding.  She also said the root exposure damage could possibly be repaired by using a product called MI Paste.  If SleepRight were to change the product so that the silicone separated top and bottom teeth all around your mouth this might be a viable product.

column13: Handy for smoothing out your feet
column14:
I placed an order for this product without checking to see if it came with a U.S. compatible power adapter. That was a mistake on my part and even though it does not come with a U.S. power adapter, I was able to find a Euro to US adapter that allows for me to charge it here in the United States. I jumped on it when I saw it because an item like this sold in stores is twice the cost of what it was being sold for here.

So, how does it work? Once fully charged it's as simple as pressing the button. The grinding wheel starts spinning and you just move it over your feet in the places you would like to smooth out. The wheel spins fast, but has a limit on the power so it does not rip your skin off. It's a very nice device and I'm extremely happy to have it. Over the years I've let my feet take a beating and this was a step in the right direction on making my feel nice.

column6: Essential oil by Morning Pep Happy with Your purchase or Your.
column14:
I absolutely adore essential oils, and lemon is no different. The scent is so uplifting and energizing, a few drops can help get you going in the morning. I mostly use it for the aromatherapy side, lemon can be a little harder on the skin if you use too much, so be sure to use a carrier oil if you do so and be sure you wear sunscreen later as it can make your skin a tad sensitive to the sun. There is no dropper in this bottle, just open and pour, so if you use one or two drops at a time, I would suggest switching your bottles of adding a dropper. If you use it for cleaning and in home made recipes like dish washing detergent or in spray cleaner, then you won't need to do this. It makes a fantastic addition to my spray vinegar cleaner. A little dawn, a decent amount of vinegar, a little water and some lemon oil. This works fantastic in place of chemicals in the kitchen. It's safe to use around kids and still kills the germs. The oil smells exactly like a fresh squeezed lemon and makes my mouth water when I smell it. It smells clean.

*I RECEIVED THIS PRODUCT TO TRY AT A DISCOUNTED PRICE IN EXCHANGE FOR AN HONEST AND UNBIASED REVIEW. EVERYTHING IN THIS REVIEW IS 100% MY OWN AND IN NO WAY INFLUENCED

I want to make sure I keep them protected, when you spend good money for beauty supplies you don't want to have to replace them, so I try and take the best care of them as I can. This helps to protect my good brushes from outside elements that can degrade them..

I recommend this makeup brush case from Hotrose for anyone who doesn't have a case to put their makeup brushes in. This is a nylon type of material makeup case,however you can use it for other things if you wish.

column6: Dove Men+Care Body Wash, Hydration Balance 18 oz
column14:
The Dove Men + Care Hydration body and face wash is a body wash with a typical, but not overbearing, "man" soap scent.

I've used a few Dove Men + Care body washes now, and this bottle works just as well as any of them. If you already like Dove's Men + Care product line and how your skin responds to it, you'll have no problems with this body wash flavor. The bottle itself has an oval shape and base, which actually works well on shower racks that are composed of wires. The elongated oval shape gives it a stable base, even on those types of shower shelves where the wires are spread out nearly an inch apart. The bottle is also easy to squeeze, and the flip-lid's hinge is durable enough to last until you empty the bottle without snapping off.

The liquid soap is a dark blue color with typical viscosity. It lathers well in a poof or washcloth and spread easily on your skin. I have mildly irritable skin, and this Dove Men + Care Hydration body soap doesn't set off any kind of reactions or blemishes for me. The scent definitely smells like what companies think a "man-soap scent" should be, but it's not nearly as powerful as some of the Axe body wash fragrances. As far as providing "hydration balance," ehh....it doesn't dry out my skin, but it's not like it's moisturizing my skin as well as lotion or something. You can obviously also use it to wash your face in a pinch, but I still opt to use a gentler, dedicated face wash on a daily basis.

In summary, this Dove Men + Care Hydration Balance body wash is a quality liquid shower soap for your daily needs. It has a scent that isn't overpowering and it lathers nicely. If you already like Men + Care body wash products, you'll probably like this one as well.

column6: Jerome Russell Punky Hair Color Creme
column13: Punky Flamingo Pink mixed with Punky Plum
column14:
I am very impressed by how vibrant these colors are and how long they last in the hair. They do start to fade out, but even the faded colors are gorgeous. My natural hair is a very dark brown, almost black so I needed to bleach my hair three complete rounds to get it light enough for the color to go over it. (About a level 8). I think that the people that are complaining about it not working or not covering their hair are the people that aren't taking the steps to lighten their hair before they apply.

I mix equal parts of the Punky Flamingo Pink and the Punky Plum to get a pretty vibrant magenta color. I also dilute the Plum with an equal part of conditioner. (So one pot pink, one pot plum, and one pot conditioner, for example.) The product itself is thick and easier to apply that most dyes. Because it is a semi-permanent stain, it is ok to leave on your hair for a long time. In fact, the longer you let it stay in your hair, the longer the color will hold and the more vibrant it will be. I apply mine in the evening, wrap my hair/head with plastic wrap, and then sleep on it and wash it out in the morning. (Be sure to put a towel over your pillow that you don't mind ruining, in case a bit of the color transfers) I re-apply every 6 weeks after bleaching my roots again. (Side note: when bleaching your roots, the bleach that touches the purple hair will turn a vibrant green color....don't worry about it. It will cover just fine once you reapply the Punky colour)

I have long hair and a lot of it, so I end up using a total of THREE 3.5oz containers of product each time. You really want to saturate the hair so that it applies evenly. In the photo shown my color had been on my hair for 4 weeks, fading it a lighter magenta color, and then I went and weaved some of the Punky Plum as well as the Punky Purple in my hair so that I had 3 different variations of color.

column6: Remington PR1285A R8 Wet & Dry Rotary Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver, Blue
column13: Not as close as a razor, but its a good shower shaver.
column14:
My last Remington was a cordless SR9130TV which I used as an emergency shaver - something to throw in my bag when I couldn't do a wet shave with a blade -- I'm not man enough to dry shave with a blade, pocket knife or office scissors, no matter the quality of the precision 5 blades. I prefer to shave in the shower whenever possible - and usually with a disposable razor. So a WetTech electric razor peaked my interest. I run through Fusion disposables at an expensive rate - so cordless electric definitely has value if its even comparable. I'm not a active electric user, so keep this in mind for my take on this one. This is a plastic lightweight rotary. Feels noticeably lighter than the older metal Remington rotary shaver - which is great, since dropping it on my feet isn't out of the question. The more composite materials will probably last longer in my hard water environment. I hit it with an overnight charge and ready for a Monday trial.

My first experience wasn't encouraging. It took almost 3 times as long to get a decent shave. I used a gel for comfort after initially just trying wet shave. It was uncomfortable with a bit of abrasion, and I wasn't getting very close. I had a 1.5 day beard by then. The gel eased the discomfort, but it took a long time to get everything reasonably close. Reading up on it tells me that my face has to be trained. After looking at the result in the mirror, I cleaned up with a razor and vowed to give it a week.

For the next few days, either my ability improved with the rotary wet shave, or my face was being trained. I continued to follow up with a razor for certain areas around my chin that don't seem to take to rotary cuts as close.. so far. I noticed that I'm using more shaving gel than with a razor, mostly because I'm reapplying. The results did improve and my shaving time did reduce. By the end of the week, I was more proficient but it didn't replace the closeness of the Fusion 5 blade razor that I commonly use. I think that if I really needed to cut the shaving cost down of my disposable habit, that a cordless that can be used in the shower is definitely my go to. The Remington seems to do well in the shower, and with more use and practice, I'll either be trained in use or my face will become smarter? I don't think it will replace the closeness of a razor, but I could use much less of them if I'm only using them for occasional touch up.

As for cleanup, I open the face of the razor after use under the shower. It's quick and easy and appears to be keeping it clean. A more thorough clean may be possible with a cleaning brush, but not letting it dry up and gunk up is probably a good daily practice and the rinse under the shower head seems to do that nicely. I still haven't recharged the razor -- trying to see how long it lasts between charges. But it's lasted a week so far and that's a good run for any daily use cordless.

The charging stand isn't anything to write home about. Don't try to charge it until its dry -- right? But when you do, it's nice that Remington now has smaller adapters that take less outlet space. It's power-strip friendly if your power-strip is "stacked" not "side-by-side". Look at pictures to see what I mean. Previous Remington came with a case, but this supplied cap is easier to store in my kit for travel.that I commonly use. column13: Does the job of hiding those grays. I'm a repeat buyer and satisfied.
column14: I've ordered this product twice before and I am getting ready to order another one. I really like this conceal spray. It has held me over when I've been late on my dye job (hiding alot of grays these days). I can go over about 2 weeks using this. It lasts all day on me. I have curly hair so I don't run my hands through my hair alot or run a brush through it after I style it in the morning, to avoid frizzies. Someone who has straight hair and runs a combs or brush through it through out the day might have an issue with it coming off, but I wouldn't know.  You really have to move your hand swiftly while spraying to avoid a dark spot of paint in one place. You have to move quickly. I cover my forehead with the other hand and sometimes I will get a little paint on my finger and nails but it washes out easily.  At first if looks darker than the rest of my hair but after a few minutes it dries and blends in with my color. The only problem I've had lately is that I have dyed my hair a dark brown with red tones and this color doesn't match as well as when I just dyed it dark brown with no red. But I have no other option as far as color goes.  I have used it on damp hair with no problem.  The bottle lasts me about two dye cycles, so thats about 25  applications, that being only because I'm really graying  :(  and I am covering more areas of my head. Of course this varies greatly on how much growth you are trying to cover.

column6: Moroccan Argan Oil for Face, Hair, Skin & Nails 100% Organic 2fl oz Fang and Whistle
column13: Miracle skin product for people with sensitive skin.
column14:
I received this product free in return for an honest review. I was fairly impressed with this item and it's packaging. The oil is contained in a nice sturdy dark glass bottle with a pump (kind of like the type that would be on a serum bottle.) I found this quite handy because I am clumsy and have knocked over and spilled numerous bottle of essential oils.

Another thing I thought added to the product was a "list of uses" for this oil. The only downfall was there was no explaination as to how to use the oil for these use. (There are instruction on amazon which I found after the fact. Would have been nice to have it in the package.) Example "for hair: deep conditon to add shine." How many drops? Wet or dry hair? Ect.

I used this product based on the "list." I put it on my hair and I don't know if I used too much but now it looks like I should probably wash it. ( I don't consider this a flaw with the product as I probably did not use it correctly.)

For Skin, it suggest "acne inflamation reducer" I put it on my acne and it's still red, however the burning sensation I usually have decreased immensly. It suggests "cutical softner" I put it only on my right hand and I could tell a significant differance. My favorite suggestion was "lip balm." I am happy to report my painful chapped lipes feel like a silky slice of heaven after ONE application a DAY LATER.
My S.O. has large guaged ears that dry out. We applied 1 squirt of oil to each ear and now they are soft and well hydrated. He even commented later that he was so impressed at how soft his ears are. ( It takes a lot for him to be impressed.)

Overall the consistancy is not too thin or think but just silky enough and is not overly greasey. When applying to the lips I was worried about taste but there was no taste. It does not have a strong or over powering smell. It does have a slight earthy smell to it.

I would actually buy this product again.

column13: Horrendous smell, you couldn't pay me to try it. NOT COCONUT
column14: The smell is horrendous, nauseating,super strong,like a bouquet of Chemicals including every smell EXCEPT COCONUT. I truly do not understand when companies use the word coconut as their primary name and description of items that do not have anything remotely coconut like. If you used coconut as an ingredient but the primary scent is lillies or roses.or.cinnamon or jet fuel or vanilla, PLEASE ADD IN UNDERSTANDABLE TERMS..."vibrant scent of jet fuel and roses" or whatever it is. Coconut cream means it smells like coconut,lightly.or strongly,it's the primary smell. My entire box of items ordered reeked of chemicals so bad I thought it spilled. It was in a sealed bag and unopened. It is so disgustingly awful I cannot even try it once. It could Give me the most gorgeous 20 year old persons hair and make me look 10 years younger and though I might consider it longer, it would still end up in the trash outside to get it out of my house. What on earth is this scented with? I am sensitive to smells and there are only a handful I can use and coconut is one of them. I do not expect all coconut items to work for me because of my immune problems which reject many things that are not supposed to be a problem. But...if it has nothing remotely COCONUT it makes me mad because it is.misleading at best and a flat out lie at worst.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Feels fresh, not sure if it's whitening
column14: I had the opportunity to try this product for free as a BzzAgent. I have previously tried a similar product from Crest, called HD White, that worked in a similar way - two tubes for two different steps. Overall, I am relatively neutral on this 3D White product. It does leave my mouth feeling fresh, and I like that it encourages me to brush for the dentist-recommended amount of time (2 minutes). The first time I tried it, I did feel a bit of tooth/gum sensitivity, which made me think that the whitening product might really be working. (I always get sensitivity with whitening products.) But, I only felt that sensitivity the very first use, and even with consistent use for several weeks, I can't say that I've noticed a major difference in the whiteness of my teeth. I do drink quite a bit of coffee, so it's possible that this toothpaste is preventing additional staining. I will continue using the product, but at this price point, I'm not sure I would buy it again.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: SUPER high quality shaver with little to no maintenance
column14:
Let me say first that I am reviewing this shaver as a promotion from Braun.

That's out of the way. I LOVED THIS SHAVER. for some background I go back and forth from beard to no beard to goatee to mutton chops so I use all kinds of different shavers. This Braun 9 series is sleek and super effective. It is waterproof (big bonus), and the shave action is super smooth with no pinching or pulling even on the longer flat hairs at the bottom of the throat. It gives a super close and comfortable shave without any real tugging or anything.

Other than the close shave my favorite thing about it is the super convenient alcohol based cleaner / charging dock. Pop the shaver open and dump the hair then just set it in the dock push a button and not worry about it again until the next shave. Being a very lazy person I loved how easy it is to keep up with.

My only drawbacks would be I think the sideburn trimmer could use a little more umph, and it can get a bit slick in the shower with the super smooth shiny surface. There is some grip on the sides but I would like a bit more. The shaver does feel sturdy though so I'm not too worried about dropping it. I see these 2 things as extremely minor though, and are immensely outweighed by the quality of shave and the easy care.

If you want a shaver that does what its supposed to do and is super easy to upkeep this one is a no brainer.

column14: We didn't want to put the toxic ingredients in deodorant on our armpits, so we tried A LOT of natural deodorants. Nothing from Whole Foods worked, sadly even Trader Joe's version didn't work. People began avoiding us for some reason. Since Amazon has been having all of the answers lately, we tried Green Tidings. Now, we can participate in society again. It holds up all day and the lavender scent is very very pleasant (not sweet or fruity, more like fresh laundry) and people tell us we smell good, and that hasn't happened in a long time. A lot of times when you get on the natural bandwagon you end up with inadequate hygiene because most eco stuff is just too weak. Green Tidings merged non-toxicity and functionality in a market of crappy "green" products and dangerous mainstream products. We can now hug people without fear. Thank you Green Tidings.

column6: Ossur Rebound Air Low Top Walker
column14:
Pros
-Plastic construction is great and light weight
-The fact that it covers your whole foot is also great
Cons
-Squeaks like crazy each time you step. the insole is attached with double sided tape to the inside of the boot, since the inside of the boot has plastic ribs in it to reduce weight, the adhesive pulls away each time you step down so it causes it to make a stick noise. I pulled out the insole and covered the adhesive in paper, the toe squeak is fixed but the main sound of the squeak appears to come from the heel where the tread attaches to the boot, but I'm not going to try to peel that apart and see what is causing it.
-The air cushion does not hold any sort of pressure, as soon as you pump it up it goes flat again within a second or two.
-The rubber part on the toe cover is starting to tear like other people have mentioned.

Will not buy again.

Also i am very fair and got 110 but it still seemed to dark for my skin down. I think they need to open up the selection for more fairer shades as there are so many shades of fair skin. I did notice even though i would set this foundation with a powder it still would feel a little to oily for my skin and i have normal skin. I would have to keep applying powder through out the day to keep the shine away that was coming through along my t zone. As a massage therapist, and doing massages all day, when i would sweat ( doing massage is very laborious) the foundation would run off my face and even though i only wore a thin layer, by the end of the day, it would be gone, and what i currently use, it does not budge.  Also, i find it a little to watery. I like a foundation on the creamer side, just my personal preference. Overall i did like this product but please remember, i bought this as a temporary fix because at the time i didn't have enough money to buy what i currently use (kat von d lock it tattoo foundation). I am in no way giving this a bad review,just stating my honest opinion.  It did the job and was good for what i needed to do.

column6: (6 Pack) NYX Wonder Pencil - Light
column13: This is definitely worth a try!
column14:
I am amazed at what this little pencil has done to my face!

I have yellow/pink skin so I selected the light. The texture of the pencil is medium - softer than many pencils but not like those really soft smudgy ones. The effect is that it is soft enough to glide across my skin, but not so soft it leaves little clumps. The tip is sharpened to a fine point but I can do broader strokes using the side of the pencil.

The effect is youthful, softly bright eyes that last all day - and yes I have somewhat moist skin and yes I am the kind of girl who touches her face constantly. It's the makeup - it's amazing!

I am wearing it in my water line, where it stays put, and also in the little dent under my eyes near my nose, where I always have purple, tired skin. This pencil lets me put just a few strokes in that delicate little area that cover the purple and reduce the appearance of the dent. I also have visible capillaries right under my nose. Again, a few strokes is all I need to cover those up without a cakey result. It looks like my skin is all one color :).

It's simply beautiful! I don't wear a lot of makeup - I prefer natural tones - just a little bit of enhancement. This pencil is that - it easily fixes all those little things near my nose and eyes that make me look old and tired, and instead it gives me a wide-eyed natural glow.

I have always lined my water line - blue, green, gray, black, brown, white - but never flesh tone... It's genius! I can't believe I never tried a bright flesh tone before but wow what a difference!

This one is a win!

column6: Mike & Mary 100% Remy Human Hair Clip in Extensions 20” Silky Straight Clip on Hair Extensions
column13: For this purpose these extensions were perfect!
column14:
I have been using extensions for over 10 years, typically I buy from a hair shop and pay any from 100-250$ for my extensions. I already had hair, brown and blonde weave extensions when I bought these. My sole purpose in buying these was to have a little bit more "blonde" color to mix into my hair extensions I already had. For this purpose these extensions were perfect!

To anyone buying these to use solely, I would highly recommend 2 or 3 orders as the hair itself is very thin. Not to say this is a bad thing, actually I find this to be a plus, because they are light weight and do not weigh down your head which is very nice as a lot of extensions will do this and cause head aches and really become not worth the pain of wearing them!

The overall quality of the hair is good, and this comes from a hair extension buyer of over 10 years. But as noted keep in mind they are very thin! If you have thick hair I honestly would not recommend them. If you have thin hair as mine, 2 or 3 pairs of these will do you perfect! I only bought one because as noted I already had hair extensions I just wanted to add to.

For 40$ the price is right! Thank you!

column13: WORTH EVERY PENNY AND THEN SOME
column14: LOVE LOVE LOVE THIS HEATING PAD!!!  I was in a very bad car accident in 2003.  I have had to have 2 back surgeries so far because my L-5, S-1 almost severed my spinal cord. I have fusions at the L-5 and S-1 now and getting ready to have another fusion at my L-4.  Unfortunately I did not have health insurance and had to wait 4 months for my first surgery and 6 months for my second this caused me to have permanent and irreversible nerve damage in my lower back and legs.  I was given my heating pad by my surgeon after my first surgery.  I live with this heating pad on my back every day for several hours a day.  This will be the first heating pad that I had to purchase.  This heating pad lasted me almost 13 years and with hours of use every single day I can not complain.  I can not believe it lasted this long with all the use it has been through.  So yes it is worth EVERY penny and the amount of heat, the coverage on my back due to its size, and the longevity of its life span is remarkable.  I would recommend this product to anyone.

column6: Leave-In Conditioner | Deep Conditioner for the Best Looking Hair Ever | Nutritive Ingredients Create Miracle Deep Leave-In Conditioner
column14:
I have extremely dry processed hair. I curl it (with a straightner ) every other day and color it about every 2-3 months. My hair is thick and a frizzy curly (without any styling or products).

I had seen this brand on Pintrest and decided to give it a try. I tried this product for the firs time on Saturday August 8th, I washed my hair and per the reviews I applied only about a quarter size amount to my damp hair. Once I applied it, I brushed my hair and slept on it wet. The conditioner is a bit thick, so you do not need to use very much. Again, I have thick hair and a quarter size amount worked perfect!

Because my hair gets oily very easily, I only applied the product to the ends of my hair + this is where I see the most damage.

The next morning my hair was dry and I proceeded to curl it like I normally do.

I was amazed by the difference I saw on my hair from just 1 use!!! My hair was soft and I did not notice the split ends as much. My brother in law even complemented me on how nice my hair looked!

I would absolutely recommend this product and will continue to use it.

I noticed some of the reviews mentioned the smell could be better. I agree, however the smell is not unberable or strong enough to where it would keep me from using this product.

Also, the amount in the jar is enough to last me for at least a year!

column6: Evening Primrose Carrier Oil. A Base Oil for Aromatherapy, Essential Oil or Massage use.
column13: Great additon to my skincare arsenal
column14:
I’ve wanted to purchase some evening primrose oil to add to my DIY skin recipes and I’m glad Plant Therapy gave me an incentive to do so sooner. Evening primrose oil is too oily to use as a carrier on its own and most recipes call for only around 10% to be mixed with another carrier like jojoba. It is best used with dry or mature skin and contains high levels of GLA essential fatty acids, useful for reducing signs of aging and eczema.

It is very rich and moisturizing, just right for people with dry skin like me! But, do use sparingly as it leaves an oily feeling on the skin.
There is a recipe for facial serum by Plant Therapy below that I am dying to try.

For Dry or Mature skin: Use up to 9 drops per ounce of Anti-age synergy in carrier of choice -OR- to 2 ounces of Evening Primrose carrier add 3 drops patchouli, 4 drops helichrysum, and 4 drops frankincense.
I also want to try to use some in a DIY body oil for my daughter who has eczema.

Very happy with my purchase.

Note: I purchased this product at a discount in exchange for an unbiased review.

column6: Garnier  Nutrisse Nourishing Color Foam
column13: Not the same Light Intense Auburn!
column14:
Beware if you've used other Garnier hair dyes, this is not the same dye color as the liquid Light Intense Auburn, it's less red and darker. I was slightly wary when I received the dye and the photos showed a darker color, but decided to go for it anyway instead of bothering with an exchange. Normally, I dye my hair closer to a true light auburn (think almost Ariel red) and use the Nutrisse Ultra Color. Despite having the same exact name, these are very different colors.

With that said, I am a big fan of the color foam in general. I tend to make a giant mess using the normal liquid hair dye, and have to rush to clean everything up before it stains everything in the bathroom. The color foam removes that concern, it's not nearly as drippy as the liquid dyes and is easy to smooth into roots and all over hair. With the liquid dyes, I always worry whether or not I'll have enough to evenly cover my hair, but with the foam this is NEVER an issue.

Final verdict, just wish this was in a brighter and more vibrant red, but it's simple to use and works great.

column6: Philips Sonicare DiamondClean Sonic Electric Rechargeable Toothbrush
column13: ... one because I felt that I was doing just fine brushing and flossing
column14:
I've read about sonic toothbrushes for years but never felt the need to purchase one because I felt that I was doing just fine brushing and flossing. A friend of mine picked up this model and raved about it. My mom, who "doesn't do technology," even said she liked her sonic toothbrush. As a result, I went all in and purchased a pair for my wife and myself with a set of extra heads.

I love it. The different settings are great as they allow my wife with sensitive teeth to use a lesser setting while I continue with the normal one. While I would never call brushing my teeth a "hard" thing to accomplish, this toothbrush definitely makes it easier. The pulse every 30 seconds tells you to switch to a different section of your mouth and provides for that dentist recommended 2 min brush time (with added time for the "whitening" if you so desire. Note: whitening setting just adds another 30 seconds of normal operation for you to focus on your more visible teeth)

The charge base works like a champ and the battery has held up solid while traveling. The travel case is very sturdy as well. Would definitely recommend.

column13: Very good quality!! Definately worth the money!
column14:
This is one of the first wigs I've ever ordered on amazon and I am so glad I did!! The curls are so gorgeous and the color is very beauiful! The last photo I have of my mom in it is the closest I could get in a picture to the real color. The photo they have provided is pretty close, just a little bit less orange and more strawberry blonde. The first two photos I've included were just to show the style of the wig. The color is much more saturated than that.

I have a 22 1/2 in. head and waist length hair so finding wigs beig enough to fit all of that is a real challenge but this wig fit me perfectly. I didn't have to hook it any to get it to fit but there are hooks for those who have a smaller head.

The length is pretty accurate to the description but the bangs are really really long. This is good so you can trim them to how you'd like but they can't be left down or else they will cover all of your face. I didn't trim mine any; I just pinned mines up and it looks great like that alone! The part shown is shown in the middle but you can move the part to the sides.

My only problems really were that the curls frizz up pretty easily especially if you're moving it around a lot and that the part looks a little fake, but these are common problems with wigs.

The wig doesn't look as natural on my skin color, since I have naturally black hair and my skin color is pretty close to the color of the wig too, but people with lighter or darker tones than me would look great in it!

column13: A Great Towel for Quick Drying!
column14:
I often shower right before work and hate going in with my hair still wet. Comfy Towels microfiber salon towels help dry my hair quicker than I thought a towel could!

Microfiber is great for cleaning and drying my car, but I never thought it would work well for my hair! The same moisture-wicking qualities I enjoy in my car towel are at play here and this towel literally sucks the water out of my strands. This towel is so soft and the perfect size to throw over my shoulder on my way into the shower.

This towel does require a bit of upkeep, but in my opinion it's nothing extraordinary. By running it through the washing machine alone at first like the instructions suggest I was able to deal with the dye running as other reviewers have mentioned. These towels are best kept together with other black microfiber items in the wash, which is proper laundry technique in the first place.

I am very impressed in the quality I found in my Comfy Towel microfiber salon towel! I did receive a sample of this product but price doesn't change how absorbent it is, nor does it effect my review,

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14: I received the product as part of a promotion from the brand, but I have been a Braun user for years. I cannot say enough about this shaver. It has the fastest blade of any shaver that I have ever owned, and that equates to a clean and fast shave. The head has 2 settings. You can lock it into place, or you can set it at free floating. The free floating setting allows the head to move and adjust to the curves of your face and neck. It gives the closest shave of any electric shaver that I have ever owned. It also has a trimmer, on the backside, for shaping and trimming. It's great for sideburns and beards. Finally, it comes with it's own cleaning system. This is great for those of us who are to lazy to manually clean our shavers. Just push a button and the shaver vibrates, as cleaning solution is released into the shaver. This ensures that the shaver is not only clean of debris, but also sanitized. It's a great shaver, at a great price. If you're like me, and just love the convenience of an electric shaver, then this is the one for you.

To me the scent is perfume-y, or even "powdery" (like talcum powder when you're getting a haircut), like a fancy soap, which isn't bad. A close second is  Palmolive stick (which is also just "soapy", but I actually really like it).  The scent would not be out of place in a barbershop, but along the same lines it's somewhat old fashioned (and not in a "timeless classic" sense, but rather in an "old geezer" sense).  The only other soaps I have are Proraso Sandalwood and Proraso Menthol as well as a lavender soap a friend made for me and Williams Mug soap (which isn't much to write home about).  P.S. I do like the form factor - a stick with a screw-on cover - great for travel. No mug needed (other than your face, ha-ha). It tends to lather well even in hard water, so if you like this scent, it's totally worth it.

column6: Microfiber Hair Towel By Luxe Beauty Essentials …
column14: I will never go back to a normal towel for my hair.  Ever.  I was really excited to try this hair towel.  I had heard of them and was curious if it would help dry my hair faster with less damage to it.  The hype is true.  It's soooo absorbent.  As soon as I took the towel out of the plastic wrap, I fell in love with the softness.  It's a super high quality plush microfiber.  It reminds me of those Kleenex tissues that have the lotion in them.  I couldn't wait to wash my hair and try it out.  I wrapped my hair up in the towel as soon as I stepped out of the shower.  It just barely covered all of my hair because I have long hair (to the middle of my back) but I liked that it wasn't heavy and bulky like typical towels.  I was only able to leave it on for maybe 10-15 minutes because we had to be somewhere.  As soon as I took it off I gently hand-dried my hair with it for a minute.  Immediately I noticed my hair was already really dry.  With an average bath towel it would take another hour to be that dry.  My hair felt really soft and happy too.  I styled it as usual and it looked great.  I am so excited to use this towel in the morning when I'm rushing to get ready for work.  I never have time to wait for my hair to dry in a normal towel so it takes forever to blow dry it and half the time it's still damp underneath because I just don't have the time.  This microfiber towel is such a big time saver for me.  It feels so luxurious as well, it made me feel like I was at the spa.  I received this product in exchange for my honest, unbiased review.  I highly recommend this hair towel to everyone, especially those who require a lot of time drying their hair.

column6: Pure Organic Raw Unrefined Organic Shea Butter, BPA Free Bottle
column14:
Very simple and attractive jar. I do think that the jar should have some kind of seal on top for better protection.
From the color, consistency and texture this is definitely raw unrefined shea butter.
Shea butter is made from nuts that comes from the tree called Vitellaria.

There are unlimited uses for shea butter such as moisturizers for skin hair nails.
All you have to do is boil a tablespoon or two of the shea butter in a double boiler. Place a bowl (heat safe) in a small pot and boil until the shea butter is melted. Add a little bit of coconut oil (1 teaspoon or so). When melted, take the bowl out of the pot and whip it to a thick consistency and lather that on your hair or skin.

I use raw shea butter for soap and lip balm making. It's so much cheaper and better quality if you make your own soap or lip balm with raw shea butter because the final product won't contain harmful chemicals.

I received a discount for the shea butter exchange for my honest and unbiased review. Thanks for reading!

column6: Phytoceramides from Sublime Beauty. 30 V-Cap Anti Aging Supplement.
column14:
I became aware of Phytoceramides rather recently, and was really excited about all the great benefits
attributed to taking them. But, because I'm gluten senstive, I was disappointed to discover that most
Phyceramides are wheat based, and therefore, I could not use them. I was delighted to find that
Sublime Beauty Phytoceramides are rice based, and consequently a product I could use.

I have been taking these capsules now for about a month, and so far I'm very pleased with the results.
About two weeks after I started taking the capsules I noticed my facial skin felt firmer and incredibly
soft and smooth. I have been using a topical Vitamin C serum as part of my daily beauty routine, and
was happy to discover that it is recommended to use along with taking the Phytoceramide capsules. The
two seem to work synergistically, resulting in a wonderfully clear, vibrant complextion. While the tiny
fine lines have diminished, it's too soon for the deeper lines on my forehead, but, I will continue
taking the capsules, and hopefully, over time, they will diminish as well.

The company's customer service is excellent, providing fast delivery, and a very informative 6 page
report detailing all about Phytoceramides. I would definitely recommend this product.

I received this product at a discount for an honest and unbiased review

column14:
Love it. Second time around ordering this product. It's changed my period so much. It's so much less hassle and I don't have to bother with anything over my 10 hour shift at work. There is some getting used to this product, figuring the suction out, and you have to be comfortable with yourself. Their website offers a lot of FAQs and answered any questions I had about it. I also watched a YouTube video but there was only one helpful video the other videos had really stupid people talking about it. (One girl went back to tampons and changed her tampon every time she peed...like obviously she doesn't know how her body works) but really you just have to gauge whether this is the right product for you and how comfortable you are with the idea. Idk but it weirds some people out.
P.s. I still wear liners with the cup because (added insurance) sometimes I don't get the suction quite right and can leak a little but it still nothing compared to how a tampon can sometimes leak.

column6: Natural Aqua Gel Cure 250ml
column14:
After searching for and trying hundreds of exfoliators 3 years later i came upon this holy grail.
Cure Natural Aqua Gel really does all it claims to do. I decided to buy it after reading some really convincing reviews, even though this is WAY over the price I usually spend on one product its totally WORTH IT!
The product is looks like a foggy kind of water and its rather runny when you put it on your hands. It also takes a while to start working but after 30seconds-1min on rubbing this baby on you face you will DEFINITELY see results. Your dead skin starts to come off in little white flakes and your face instantly starts to feel a lot smoother. This is a really GENTLE product unlike most. Its like rubbing water or gel on your face rather than most exfoliators which are rocky and rough which may leave your face even worse off, especially if you have sensitive skin like me. Its the perfect fit for overly sensitive skin.
Also, keep in mind your face and hands have to be completely dry before using this product or else it won't work. If you have sweaty palms or live in a humid area then i maybe wouldn't recommend this product.

Its been around 2 months since i've started using this product (twice a week) and i see a great difference in my skin. I'm breaking out a lot less often (keep in mind this won't cure acne, its not really meant to either), the acne that i do get is a lot smaller in size, and my old scars are ALL VANISHING! I've had these scars on my face for years and nothing worked to get rid of them except this!

I really recommend this if you have sensitive skin and are looking for an exfoliator! :-)

column6: Schmidt's Natural Deodorant
column14: At first I loved this product, it really worked at covering up my odor. I would not stink at all, I would wear it all day even after my boot camp workouts. But the ultimate test was when i went to Disneyland and it was very hot, this deodorant did not stand a chance......i was very self conscious and very stinky by mid day. I have really bad BO I inherited it from my mom- thanks mom......  :( So any ways it works really well but then the rash came along....my armpits were red, itchy, super dry and then they turned really black. Now I did read reviews about this, depending on the color of your skin, your pigmentation has something to do with it blah blah blah. I used this product for about a month and I waited for it to go away. It would go away and then come back till I had about enough. This isn't my first time trying to go organic on deodorant. I've tried Toms, Kiss my Face, & EO organic Lavender Spray. I thought I hit the jackpot when I read about the top ten organic deodorants on mindbodygreen website.  I still wanted to go organic so I did some research and I found another brand of deodorant without baking soda (brand:Meow Meow Tweet). And guess what it works way better than this!!! My armpits are no longer black or red they are actually getting lighter!!! So ladies, I would do research and look at different brands. I do love the smell of this and the lavender sage deodorant. Hope this review helps!!!

column6: Modern Organic Products Conditioner for Fine Hair, Lemongrass, 10.1 Fluid Ounces
column14:
I LOVE LOVE LOVE this conditioner. I'd like to preface this review with a little bit about my skin/hair type and why I bought this in the first place: I have extremely sensitive skin. Recently I have been having problems with all conditioners breaking my scalp, back, and shoulders out no matter how thoroughly I rinsed. I have long, thick, dry hair, but an oily/combo skin type. Prior to trying this and the matching shampoo ( ) I used Free and Clear Shampoo and Conditioner, and it still broke me out, made me itchy, and didn't really work. I tried this brand after doing some googling and someone recommending it after having a similar problem.

I use this daily and I feel it rinses better than other conditioners, which seem to stay in your hair no matter how much you rinse. Even though I rinse most of it out it still makes my hair soft, shiny, and brushable. It is not a super conditioner, so if you have a rats nest in the back of your hair this will not remedy your problem. The smell is very light, it almost has no smell at all. It does not leave a scent in my hair at all. It helps me with my brushing but its still an ordeal with long hair. It helps with frizziness and with control while styling. Most of all, IT IS SO GOOD TO MY SKIN. No break outs, not itchy, just soft hair.

Overall, I am SO happy with this product. I would recommend this product over and over again. I have bought it more than once.

column6: Hair Tamer Sectioning and Gripping Croc Hair Styling Clips 12 Pack
column13: Amazing for Holding Lots of Hair!
column14:
My kid sister got married and came to me to do her hair before her reception. She wanted to dye her hair for the first time, and she wanted to try an ombre style. While the procedure was a bit intimidating, these styling clips from Hair Tamer made it so easy!

Creating an ombre style requires a lot of sectioning and clipping to keep the dye consistent. These 4" clips have two hinges to help them easily grab onto thick sections of hair. The small teeth kept these clips from sliding while I was working and the spring hinge was easy to open one-handed!

Of course these clips are great for much more than special hair occasions. Since they hold such a large amount of hair I've found them to be perfect for when I wash my face! A quick twist and one clip is all it takes to hold back my entire long, straight mane. Thicker hair would probably require more than one clip, but luckily this set comes with six!

Hair Tamer has made a wonderful hair clip that I'm excited to keep using! I was provided with a sample of this product but price doesn't change how well they hold hair, nor does it effect my review.

column13: Keeping Sweat and Smell a Secret!
column14: Disclaimer: I received a sample of this deodorant from Secret for free through BzzAgent.com. I used to be a big Secret fan when I was younger. It was my go-to Deodorant brand all through high-school, but I switched to Dove and Degree for some reason. When I received my sample of Secret, I instantly remembered how much I have always liked the Secret scent. The fresh-clean scent isn't too potent and makes it smell like you're fresh from the shower. The deodorant formula dries quickly, so you don't have to worry about getting it on your clothes. I feel like the deodorant did a great job of lasting for a long time and giving me sweat and odor protection. Even after a sweaty game of tennis I felt like my armpits still  had that fresh from the shower smell. I love that the clear formula avoids those pesky white stains on your clothes and armpits as well. The only issue I have with this deodorant is the dial you have to use to push out the deodorant from the tube. I feel like using the dial, I always get either too much or too little, so that is the only flaw in the product design I would like the Secret brand to work on. Either way, I love this deodorant and it reminded me why I used to use it. I'm definitely considering switching back to the Secret brand!

column14: I have fine hair that gets greasy if I don't wash it, and I use dry shampoo occasionally if I have to leave the house without a shower.  This stuff was recommended by my hairstylist, and it does give texture and volume. However, it makes my hair feel dirty.  It’s like spraying powdered clay or something in the hair.  And then it is hard to wash out – I can feel it in my hair when I shampoo, and even after lathering my hair twice, it still feels gross.  Granted, I rarely use hair products, so I am sensitive to anything that feels heavy or chunky in my hair. I have used Garnier Fructis dry shampoo, which is much lighter and cleaner feeling, while still giving volume and eliminating greasiness. It also has a nicer scent.  I would recommend that product over this one, especially if you’re used to having your hair feel soft and clean.

column6: Hotrose® White Big Round Foundation Brush for Girls
column13: Hotrose White Big Round Foundation Brush for Girls
column14:
I received this white big round foundation brush for girls from Hotrose to tes that this t, and review. I am very happy to report this foundation brush is a very good quality brush that is used to apply powder foundation, or face powder to set your make-up. This is not the type of brush you would use to apply liquid foundation, you would do much better to use a sponge to apply liquid foundation. It blends the foundation in much better that way and you don't end up with a line a to around your face, or a 'mask' look. This brush has short hair and this helps to save the amount of powder foundation that you use each time. The bristles themselves are super soft and non- irritating, they are made from a hypo-allergenic material. I didn't have any problems with them making my skin itch or break out. I would be very happy to receive this as a gift from someone, so in my opinion this would make an excellent gift idea for teens, moms, and others wanting to update their make-up brushes. It is very easy to take care of this brush, you simply hand wash the bristles with some baby shampoo, or if have some make-up brush cleaner that will work as well. (It is gentle enough) Then rinse really well, until the water runs clear (no more bubbles) then allow it to air dry completely before using again.

In my opinion I completely recommend this big white round foundation brush, it is a great quality brush that anyone would be happy to have in their make-up kit. It makes for a great gift idea for teens, moms, and anyone wanting to update their make-up kits. The bristles are synthetic fiber so you can be pretty sure most people are safe from breaking out from associated with these type of bristles. Plus they are easy to clean as well.

-* I was provided with this Big Round foundation Brush without cost so I could test and provide an unbiased review of this product for the Hotrose company. All opinions are 100% honest, true, and my own.*-

column6: Significant Beauty Anti Aging Clear Skin Facial Serum with 20% Vitamin C - 1 Oz. BEST NATURAL serum – Better than face, neck & eye creams or moisturizers for your blemishes, dark spots & wrinkles. For day, night, men & women - With Retinol, B3, MSM.
column13: Wonderful, save numerous products and just use this one........
column14:
Very impressed with this product so far. Packaged in a 1 ounce cobalt blue bottle with a dropper. When I opened it, it smelled amazing, not strong and doesn't linger, just enough to "make you feel good". The smell is Ylang Ylang I think, but then again, I love that smell, I use it as an EO all the time for different things. Serum is watery, which is normal for a lot of serums, but the dropper makes it so easy to place a drop on each cheek, forehead and chin and massage in. Then you can add a couple drops here and there under eyes or around lips in areas that might need a bit more attention. By using the dropper this way, you don't waste a drop. It absorbs very quickly and leave no oil or residue. You can continue with moisturizer and make up in just a minute. I have used it for 4 days now, morning and night. I had previously been using a Vit C serum days and a retinol serum nights, since this serum has both ingredients included, it makes it much easier than having 2 separate bottle and saves the cost also of separate serums. I am including a pic of the ingredient list since it is so wonderful. The other oils in it are all healing, soothing, anti aging, moisturizing and skin toning for uneven pigmentation. If had left my skin, soft, smooth, glowing and just looks healthy. Can't say about the skin tone yet, but I am working on it. I have a small dark spot under one eye so testing it there to see if it lightens it any at all. I have moderate sensitive skin and have not had any irritation at all. This serums with all the ingredients it has, the effect it had on my skin so far, I believe it is a keeper and I highly recommend it.

column6: Revlon 1875W Rectractable Cord, Fold & Go Hair Dryer
column13: Save your money - only lasted a month!
column14:
Do not purchase this! Save your money and buy a different brand. I bought this hair dryer about a month ago bc my previous Revlon that I had for all of 6 months started shorting out (should have been a red flag after only 6 months). But..i bought this one bc of the retractable cord - thought that would solve my shorting out issues. Well...I almost returned this dryer immediately after taking it out of the box...I could BAREL

column13: A full day in the hot glaring sun without a hint of sunburn on very sensitive skin ....
column14:
[[VIDEOID:557f68c0a3e744e25c8ecb2a37c16458]]André Lorent Sunscreen is just what I was looking for in a suncreen, something that offered up strong protection from the sun, but didn't have toxic ingredients. Mind you, I'm not up on the chemical properties of various things, but I do know that Coppertone is out and paraben-free is in. My generation is now having to deal with skin cancers of all types from overexposure to the sun.

My son has very sensitive skin and his generation has been well-informed about the result of excessive UV rays. Yesterday was a heavy work day for him, out in the glaring sun all day long. He asked if I had any suncreen and this was exactly what he wanted. I think he thought I'd show up with some two dollar sunscreen with an SPF of 15.

The André Lorent Sunscreen is perfect for him because he has very sensitive skin and many lotions simply don't agree with him. If he was going to be out in the sun all day, he not only needed protection from the UV rays, but also something that was a moisturizer. He slathered it on from head to toe because he was only going to have time for one application.

It is fragrance-free, but does have some natural fragrance to it that I can smell. It didn't bother either on of us at all, but if you're ultra-sensitive to fragrances, take a pass. The day was long, the sun high in the sky, but at the end of the day all was well. He didn't have a single patch of burn and was quite satisfied with the performance. I'm not sure how this would perform at the beach, but he certainly perspired heavily and still got the protection I wanted to see.

It's very pricey but so worth it. I can't wait to use it once or twice more. To really build in this tan. It does an absolutely amazing job.

Shipping: I qualified for free shipping and it still came in exactly two days after ordering. :)

Well over 5 stars.

column6: Andis UltraEdge Blade Size 1 3/4 #65685
column14:
As a barber and an Andis fan, I've enjoyed having more blades just on either side of what for me is the most useful blade— the 1.5. It has required me however, to create a marking system to identify them from each other because they go face down on my tool stand. The wrong side. See photo

My new 1–3/4 blade is however marked incorrectly at 4mm, instead of what the package correctly indicates of 4.8 mm. It's clear to my trained eye that it's not a 4mm #2. For those of us familiar with our now archaic Amero-English measurement called the inch, this system goes by 1/8 inch (2.4 mm) increments mostly— getting smaller toward the shorter blades. This blade fills the gap between the 1 1/2 and the 2.
God help us with this ridiculous sizing system that is illogical. . The 2 is correctly named at 1/4 inch. As for the 3 1/2— half of what? it's 3/8ths of an inch exactly, therefore it's a 3. The 3-3/4 is really a 4 because it's 1/2 inch, 4 eighths is a 4, in my mind. They finally came to their senses and called the newer bigger blades by an actual measurements, 5/8ths and 3/4ths of an inch. I of course call them the 5 and 6.
Screw it, go by mm— IF ANDIS COULD GET ONE SYSTEM RIGHT!
Perhaps my mis-marked blade will become a collector item...
Look out for the animal sizes they're the same as human blades but different markings yet, usually starting with a capitol A

column13: Newer, but may not be better than the old model
column14: Had the older, square-er model for about 10 years.  The batteries exploded inside the battery compartment which destroyed the connection. Very sad day :(.  This newer model seems to run quieter and spin faster than my previous Nail Genie Jr.  It only requires two batteries instead of three.  The redesign of the hand-held part makes it more comfortable to hold.  It doesn't seem to work as efficiently/quickly as my old one. I don't like that the new box is just cardboard (previous box was plastic laminated heavier cardboard) and is too shallow to allow the device with attachments to fit inside for storage.  This means I have to disassemble/reassemble the machine every time I use/put away the device.  Before, it was much easy to open the box, insert the attachments and do my nails.  Now I have to open the box, take out all the parts, assemble the machine, use it and take it all apart again.  However, the same design I had before was about USD20 more than I paid for the new design, so there's that.  Overall I am pleased I bought this Nail Genie.

This stuff is so great I can use it before the shower.... just put a thin coat on and immediately start shaving.  It's soothing and because it's clear you can see exactly what you're doing which is great if you have any sort of beard your trying to keep.  There's different scents this product comes in and the coconut lime is my personal favorite.  I went ahead and bought the 4-pack since it ends up a great deal vs buying them at the local hippie grocery store.

column6: Skin Sake 3577601 Athletic
column14: I'm an ultra distance runner and I live in a hot and humid state.  I've tried A LOT of products in the search for bra (and other) chafe and rash prevention.  Many worked fine, but for longer runs and races, reapplication was difficult under sweaty conditions.  I've tested Skin Sake under extreme conditions and it's the only one I use now. I have used it during 24 hour races in hot weather and never had to reapply at all!  I had zero chafing.  I recently used it in a multi-day event and went as long as 28 hours without reapplication and it still worked.  It kept my hydration vest from rubbing as well.  I also used it in a pinch to lube my feet during that race, not as good as my regular foot lube (however, my socks were soaking wet and full of sand, I was asking a lot), but it worked fine. I will say, for me it's a bit of an effort to squeeze it out of the tube, it's thick like diaper rash cream, but it is well worth it.  I just slather it on my whole torso before getting dressed and I don't have to worry about it again.

column13: I'm officially converted to a Gel Deodorant Lover!
column14:
I've always preferred dry solid deodorants/antiperspirant. I was skeptical about trying Secret Outlast Gel Deodorant/Antiperspirant for this reason. When I received a free sample through BzzAgent I was pleasantly surprised from the time I put it on until the time I went to bed. In the warm summer heat, it was a refreshing feeling and the scent is amazing.

It lasted through an almost 5 mile walk starting at 9 a.m. in July in Georgia, then through the rest of my day and night. I've definitely found my new deodorant/antiperspirant. I'm very loyal once I find a brand I like. Over the past 20+ years, I've only become extremely attached to two. In between those times, I was always on the hunt for my go-to deodorant/antiperspirant.

I'm still puzzled by the fact that I actually LOVE this gel. I can quite pinpoint what it is, though the cool, fresh feeling and scent are one of the first things that struck me. If you're not a fan of gel deodorant/antiperspirant, you might want to give it a try just in case.

As I try to use up the last of my invisible solids, I feel like I'm trying to rub two things together that weren't meant to be, kinda like the feeling of two same sided magnets (positive to positive -- ya know how they repel each other).

column13: Love Cover Girl Eye Liners, just not this color.
column14:
In the past I have used and liked Cover Girl Perfect Point Eye Liner. I normally used the Charcoal color, but decided to change things up and get brown, as it is softer and less harsh looking than the black. I should have researched more and bought the espresso color, but bought the chestnut instead.

I did not realize how light brown this color would really be. It is a very light brown, and upon applying it to my waterline, it doesn't really show up. It does not look like I have eye liner on (at least enough for my tastes) and pressing harder does not make a difference. I have dark brown eyes and very fair skin. I am an eyeliner fiend and was really disappointed I couldn't get this eye liner to show up the way I anticipated.

I would not recommend this shade for lining your waterline. I have not used it on upper lid, but I imagine it would work just fine.

It is not water proof.

Being able to twist up the pencil instead of sharpening is a lifesaver.

In general, I still like this product very much, just not the chestnut shade.

column14:

It effectively removes your makeup, and keeps your skin bright and clear. However, it makes your skin squeaky clean, which I love, but I know some people actually like the creaminess (or oiliness in my book) that some cleansers leave. I'd recommend this cleanser for all normal to oily skins and only for dry skin if you wear a lot of makeup. My skin tends to be combination but I have a whole process of moisturizers I use after my cleanser so for cleansing purposes, I want it all off!

column6: eb5 Intense Moisture Anti-Aging Cream
column13: Does a decent job, but has some negatives
column14:
From my wife Sarah: Very simply, this does a decent job of moisturizing and is made of some cleaner ingredients than most products, but it's got some issues.

Here's what I like:

- I love that it's gluten free and fragrance-free. It's also paraben-free, vegan, and non-GMO. That's fantastic, uncommon and very difficult to find. I'm very sensitive and it does not cause me any allergic reactions.

Here's what I don't care for:

- I wish it had a better texture. While it does a nice job of moisturizing, I don't like the heavy feel of it, especially on my nose and hands. It's kind of oily and thick, and I feel like I have to wash my hands to get it off my fingers after. Still, after I rub it into the rest of my face it seems to do a decent job of moisturizing.

- I don't care for the fact that you can't use it around your eyes. In fact it says that you must avoid your eyes, lids and lashes. Naturally anything going on my face is going to make its way to my eyes, even in very small amounts, so that concerns me. I would also have liked to have the ability to use it in my under eye area.

- Though it has some natural ingredients, it also has some of the chemical-sounding ingredients you'll find in non-natural brands.

Ultimately, I've been using it for about 5 days, and haven't noticed any real changes other than the fact that my skin feels moisturized. If you're looking for a moisturizing product that's free of all the things I listed above, this will work. For those with oily skin this may be too much.

The result was a collection of smudges on the silk lining of an expensive purse, which is now at a good dry cleaner who assures me that the stains can be removed.  Forgiving soul that I am, I am ordering another one of the rich Rico and it will leave home with me only in a protective plastic bag and probably in a less expensive purse.  I'm going to all this trouble because I REALLY like this product.  I wish there were more than three colors offered by Amazon, but Rico is special enough to be perfect for most occasions.

I usually just use pure Vitamin E Oil under my sunscreen, but now that I have this serum I will definitely be using it instead. On days when I know that I'll be out in the sun a lot, I will use this serum after applying my toner. After applying this serum, I will put on my sunscreen and I am ready to go! This serum has a pleasant smell and the glass dropper helps in the ease of use. It also absorbs quickly into my skin and I highly recommend it for people who are looking for a non-oily moisturizer to wear under sunscreen or makeup!

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column14: I received a free sample of this deodorant through BzzAgent, courtesy of Secret. After using it for a little over a week while on a summer family trip, I will say that this deodorant did okay, but definitely wouldn't last 48 hours for me. I loved the smell of this deodorant and that it left absolutely no white marks behind. I also loved that, as a gel, it wasn't at all sticky. While a good portion of the time I was using this deodorant, It lasted all day, or at least most of the day, on some of the more active days, I found that I needed to reapply before the day was over because it wasn't helping to control the odor and perspiration as well. While this deodorant may suffice on my less active days, It definitely doesn't seem to do the trick quite as well when I'm on the move. As a side note, I have always had a bit of a difficult time finding deodorants that control my odor and perspiration while I'm active.

column14:
Everyone knows thorough cleansing is the starting line for any type of skin care/rejuvenation/recovery etc. I've been using this for about a week now (once a day, every night) and this has been the best cleansing experience ever. (I use it only at night times because I've initially done twice a day and it felt a bit irritating to my skin.)

After using this, there's only about 5~10% left of how many visibly clogged pores I used to have and my pores shrunk to less than half of the size they used to be. Skin care products absorb much better, I feel much more clean, and even my redness from rosacea seems to be gradually getting better, a little less red!

This is not a magic wand that turns your skin into something it isn't overnight. But with consistent use, I'd say it's definitely something worth investing in. It lets whatever else you do to take good care of your skin do its job.

This is good for all ages. Teens and adults alike need to take care of their skin. This would make a great gift! I got this at a reduced price in exchange for an HONEST and UNBIASED review

column13: Simply the best serum out there - AND it's all natural! Cannot be beat!
column14:
Absolutely SUPERB product! Great for everyday use for soft, silky hair and an excellent pre-product/hairspray/texturizing spray. Also does a fantastic job taming the frizz!

I use it every night after I get out of the shower and just run two or three pumps through my long hair (focusing on the roots). I let my hair dry overnight, so when I wake up in the morning and it has dried, it's soft, silky, and (the best part) - not greasy! Many serums or oil leave behind that greasy residue, but this product doesn't leave any trace that you're wearing it - even if you put it on dry hair. I'll often run it through my dry hair as a detangler or to help reduce the little frizzies on the crown of my head. I make an extra effort to run a pump or two more in the night before I know I'll be doing a lot to my hair (major curls, lots of straightening, product, etc) to protect it - and I've noticed it reduces the feel of hairspray or texturizing spray while still letting the products do their jobs.

The bottom line is: worth. every. penny.

column13: There are no bargains with natural diamond.
column14: Amazon asked for a review. There are no bargains with natural diamond.  The Certificate and ad state a clarity of I-1.  There are a dozen different grading agencies, and some grading overlaps. A grading agency was not specified.  When buying an I-1 I reasonably expect naturals, veils, other flaws, and dark inclusions of other minerals like hematite, garnet, etc.  After all, the "I" stands for "Included".  They range from I-1 to I-3, the latter best used for masonry saws and quarrying equipment.  I do not consider a significant surface-reaching void on the crown to be allowable in an I-1.  However, since the grading agency is unknown, I feel there is not much to do about it, but I would bet my lunch it was not the GIA or IGI. She'll like them -They are real. Of course they are real. If they were Moissanite, they would be VVS, and the color would not be as good.  If they were CZ, they would be perfect. But given the clarity of these, the inclusions do affect brilliance, dispersion, and light return. Either of the above would outshine these.  There is an old saying about diamonds:  "If you want to know the true value of one, buy it.  Then sell it the next day." If one wishes to spend in this budget range, consumers should seriously consider Moissanite, the new silicon carbide simulant. Between the new synthetic diamond processes, that have already rendered natural diamond obsolete for industrial use, and ongoing improvements in Lab Diamond processes, there are only 5-10 years left to these prices, anyway. Anyone who considers a natural diamond less than 2 carats and less than VS Ideal Tokarsky Cut an investment will be disappointed. So, I will shrug, she'll be happy, it'll end well.  She has plenty of diamonds anyway.

column14:
These tunnels came fast and are incredibly comfortable!
Pros:
-Comfortable
-Very thin. This gives the illusion that your ears are bigger than they really are - which is nice if you want the option to close your ears in the future! (However, this could be a downside for some.)
-Very quick shipment/delivery
-Quality silicone, doesn't fall out
Cons:
-Difficult to get in at first
-Keep in mind that they are very thin. There is a chance that they can crease. Some customers experienced defects with their tunnels but mine came intact!
Overall, I would recommend these to anyone with stretched lobes. I included a picture for reference. (I'm at 2g)

Ana Silver Co Rare Mexican Fire Opal, Orange Kyanite 925 Sterling Silver Pendant 1 5/8\"	Jewelry	1	0	0	N	N	Orpiment is a dangerous mineral: buyer beware! Now calling it orange kyanite...	I should note that I love this vendor. I have bought three pendants from them and love the quality of the jewelry. I usually do research on the materials used before purchase, and orpiment was named one of the ten most dangerous minerals due to its high arsenic content. I can't believe that they are using it in jewelry! if you don't believe me, look it up online, and several sites mention that it is dangerous to handle, let alone to use as pendants or rings. Ana Silver company, please stop using this material. It is 61% arsenic by weight. Update: they are now calling it orange kyanite, so which is it? this is the same piece, so either the material name was wrong to begin with, or you are calling it something else to cover up that it's dangerous.	2015-08-10

column6: Rose Gold and Rhodium Plated Sterling Silver Two Tone Diamond Filigree Hoop Earrings (1/10cttw, I-J Color, I2-I3 Clarity)
column14:
These are quite appealing in their design, with their lovely rose gold color and delicate filligree swirls. Now that I've seen them in person, I can happily say that they actually look better in person than they do in the online picture. The quality seems quite good, and the little swirl design is quite well-made, and looks smooth and perfect.

As for the other aspects of the earrings, they are smaller in person than I expected. They measure about 0.75" across by 0.87" high, and are relatively flat (as expected). The hinge on the ear wire part works well, but I must mention that anyone with large or fat earlobes might have trouble wearing these (the space for your earlobe is only 0.25" wide). I'll also mention that the weight is pretty light – one earring weighs only 0.1 of an ounce.

The only real issue I had was that the rose gold color, while very pretty, doesn't look good with my skin tone. I have a bit of a tan skin tone, and the rose gold seems to blend right into it, and doesn't look quite right on me. Still, I can't blame the earrings for that since they are exactly as advertised. Anyway, if the picture and the description appeals to you, go ahead and get these – you won't be disappointed!

This charm is sturdy and will not break. It looks exactly like the picture. I was impressed with the detail included in this little charm.

If you are a collector of charms then this might be something to consider if you are looking for a Washington D.C. charm.
